label: meiotic telophase II spermatocyte
definition: spermatocyte undergoing meiotic telophase II

label: leptotene
definition: The cell cycle phase which is the first stage of prophase I in meiosis, and during which the chromosomes first become visible.

label: biological_process
definition: A biological process represents a specific objective that the organism is genetically programmed to achieve. Biological processes are often described by their outcome or ending state, e.g., the biological process of cell division results in the creation of two daughter cells (a divided cell) from a single parent cell. A biological process is accomplished by a particular set of molecular functions carried out by specific gene products (or macromolecular complexes), often in a highly regulated manner and in a particular temporal sequence.

label: optic chiasm
definition: A decussation of the diencephalon where the fibers of the optic nerve cross

label: parenchymal musculature
definition: Muscles that are present through the mesenchyme, inclusing dorsal-ventral muscles, intestinal muscles and pharynx muscles.

label: negatively regulates
definition: Process(P1) negatively regulates process(P2) iff: P1 terminates P2, or P1 descreases the the frequency of initiation of P2 or the magnitude or rate of output of P2.

label: negatively regulates
definition: Process(P1) negatively regulates process(P2) iff: P1 terminates P2, or P1 descreases the the frequency of initiation of P2 or the magnitude or rate of output of P2.

label: biological regulation
definition: Any process that modulates a measurable attribute of any biological process, quality or function.

label: has developmental potential involving
definition: x has developmental potential involving y iff x is capable of a developmental process with output y. y may be the successor of x, or may be a different structure in the vicinity (as for example in the case of developmental induction).

label: meiotic telophase I spermatocyte
definition: spermatocyte undergoing meiotic telophase I

label: single fertilization
definition: The union of male and female gametes to form a zygote.

label: core
definition: Core is an instance of a grouping of terms from an ontology or ontologies. It is used by the ontology to identify main classes.

label: left-right axis
definition: Axis perpendicular to both the anteroposterior and dorsoventral axis that runs from the left side of the animal, through the medial region (center) and out to the right side.

label: left-right axis
definition: An axis that bisects an organism from left to right sides of body, through a sagittal plane.

label: oocyte
definition: A female germ cell that has entered meiosis.

label: G2 phase  oogonial stem cell
definition: oogonial stem cell undergoing mitotic G2 phase

label: perturbation
definition: An event or occurrence that causes damage to a tissue or organ.

label: phosphate-containing compound metabolic process
definition: The chemical reactions and pathways involving the phosphate group, the anion or salt of any phosphoric acid.

label: negative regulation of reproductive process
definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of reproductive process.

label: negative regulation of embryonic development
definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of embryonic development.

label: oviduct epithelium
definition: Ciliated epithelium lining the oviduct.

label: definitive organism subdivision
definition: Anatomical structure which is a subdivision of a whole adult or juvenile organism, consisting of components of multiple anatomical systems.

label: germ cell
definition: 1. A gamete (as an egg or sperm cell) or one of its antecedent cells. 2. A mature male or female germ cell usually possessing a haploid chromosome set and capable of initiating formation of a new diploid individual by fusion with a gamete of the opposite sex.

label: testis lumen
definition: lumen which is part of the testis

label: nuclear outer membrane
definition: The outer, i.e. cytoplasm-facing, lipid bilayer of the nuclear envelope; continuous with the endoplasmic reticulum of the cell and sometimes studded with ribosomes.

label: metaphase spermatogonial stem cell
definition: spermatogonial stem cell undergoing mitotic metaphase

label: negative regulation of meiotic cell cycle
definition: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the rate or extent of progression through the meiotic cell cycle.

label: embryo stage
definition: A life cycle stage that starts with fertilization and ends with the fully formed embryo.

label: pharynx inner epithelium surface
definition: The epithelial surface lining the interior of the pharynx, facing the lumen.

label: spermatid
definition: A male germ cell that develops from the haploid secondary spermatocytes. Without further division, spermatids undergo structural changes and give rise to spermatozoa.

label: dorsal midline
definition: The median line/plane of bilateral symmetry along the anteroposterior axis on the dorsal surface of the animal.

label: regulation of mitotic nuclear division
definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of mitosis.

label: neuropeptidergic neuron
definition: A neuron that produces and releases neuropeptides at chemical synapses.

label: positive regulation of cellular process
definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of a cellular process, any of those that are carried out at the cellular level, but are not necessarily restricted to a single cell. For example, cell communication occurs among more than one cell, but occurs at the cellular level.

label: commissural neuron
definition: A neuron that has an axon which crosses the midline.

label: commissure
definition: A bundle of nerve fibers crossing from one side to the other side of the brain or spinal cord.

label: ovary nerve plexus
definition: Nerve plexus surrounding the ovary.

label: ready for release
definition: Class has undergone final review, is ready for use, and will be included in the next release. Any class lacking "ready_for_release" should be considered likely to change place in hierarchy, have its definition refined, or be obsoleted in the next release.  Those classes deemed "ready_for_release" will also derived from a chain of ancestor classes that are also "ready_for_release."

label: molecular_function
definition: A molecular process that can be carried out by the action of a single macromolecular machine, usually via direct physical interactions with other molecular entities. Function in this sense denotes an action, or activity, that a gene product (or a complex) performs. These actions are described from two distinct but related perspectives: (1) biochemical activity, and (2) role as a component in a larger system/process.

label: catalytic activity
definition: Catalysis of a biochemical reaction at physiological temperatures. In biologically catalyzed reactions, the reactants are known as substrates, and the catalysts are naturally occurring macromolecular substances known as enzymes. Enzymes possess specific binding sites for substrates, and are usually composed wholly or largely of protein, but RNA that has catalytic activity (ribozyme) is often also regarded as enzymatic.

label: testis primordium
definition: This primordium develops into testis

label: melanin pigment granule
definition: pigment granule which is part of the eumelanin

label: melanosome
definition: A tissue-specific, membrane-bounded cytoplasmic organelle within which melanin pigments are synthesized and stored. Melanosomes are synthesized in melanocyte cells.

label: chromatoid body
definition: A membrane-less, cytoplasmic ribonucleoprotein granule present in neoblasts and germ cells implicated in post-transcriptional regulation. The RNA helicase DHH1/RCK, Tudor, SmB, methylated substrates of PRMT5, PIWI-3 and Germinal Histone H4 localize to chromatoid bodies in neoblasts.

label: cell-cell contact zone
definition: Extended zone of intimate apposition between two cells containing one or more types of intercellular junctions.

label: sensory system
definition: Anatomical system that overlaps the nervous system and is responsible for receiving and processing sensory information.

label: has component process
definition: w 'has process component' p if p and w are processes,  w 'has part' p and w is such that it can be directly disassembled into into n parts p, p2, p3, ..., pn, where these parts are of similar type.

label: acidophilic gland cell
definition: One of two distinct histochemical classes of gland cells, these can be found throughout the body but primarily form clusters of subepidermal marginal adhesive glands along the dorsoventral border of the animal.

label: involved in negative regulation of
definition: c involved in regulation of p if c is involved in some p' and p' negatively regulates some p

label: diplotene stage spermatocyte
definition: spermatocyte undergoing diplotene

label: posterior region
definition: Three dimensional compartment along the anteroposterior axis that is closer to the tail rather than the head, from the anterior boundary of the pharyngeal pouch to the tip of the tail.

label: posterior region
definition: Anatomical region posteriorly located on the body or body part.

label: progenitor cell
definition: A cycling neoblast and/or post-mitotic cell that is primed or irreversibly committed to a tissue-specific differentation program

label: develops into
definition: inverse of develops from

label: develops_into
definition: inverse of develops from

label: epithelium
definition: The avascular cellular layers that cover body surfaces and cavities and may form glands.

label: has regulatory component activity
definition: A 'has regulatory component activity' B if A and B are GO molecular functions (GO_0003674), A has_component B and A is regulated by B.

label: transferase activity
definition: Catalysis of the transfer of a group, e.g. a methyl group, glycosyl group, acyl group, phosphorus-containing, or other groups, from one compound (generally regarded as the donor) to another compound (generally regarded as the acceptor). Transferase is the systematic name for any enzyme of EC class 2.

label: postero-ventral region
definition: Anatomical region that overlaps the posterior and ventral regions of a body or body part.

label: dopaminergic neuron
definition: A neuron that expresses the neurotransmitter dopamine.

label: pharynx epithelium
definition: Epithelia associated with the pharynx organ.

label: meiotic G2 phase spermatocyte
definition: spermatocyte undergoing meiotic G2 phase

label: regulation of signal transduction
definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of signal transduction.

label: meiotic telophase II
definition: The cell cycle phase which follows anaphase II of meiosis and during which the chromosomes arrive at the poles of the cell and the division of the cytoplasm starts.

label: mitochondrion
definition: A spherical to rod shaped organelle that generates the majority of a cell's supply of ATP via cellular respiration. Mitochondria have their own genome and consist of outer and inner membranes, the latter folds inward to form cristae. This folding increases the surface area of the membrane and thus increases the space available to produce ATP. The inner and outer membranes are separated by an intermembrane space, and the inner membrane encloses the matrix.

label: flame cell
definition: Terminal structure of the protonephridia unit, capping the proximal tubules. Flame cells are defined by the filtration weir‚ or filtration diaphragm, which consists of closely apposed strands of cytoplasm surrounding a central cilia bundle, and by numerous microvilli between weir and cilia. Positive for acetyated tubulin.

label: G1 phase spermatogonial stem cell
definition: spermatogonial stem cell undergoing mitotic G1 phase

label: post-pharyngeal region
definition: Posterior to the pharynx.

label: postero-dorsal region
definition: Anatomical region that overlaps the posterior and dorsal regions of the body or body part.

label: has component
definition: w 'has component' p if w 'has part' p and w is such that it can be directly disassembled into into n parts p, p2, p3, ..., pn, where these parts are of similar type.

label: has component
definition: w 'has component' p if w 'has part' p and w is such that it can be directly disassembled into into n parts p, p2, p3, ..., pn, where these parts are of similar type.

label: somatic cell
definition: One of the cells of the body that compose the tissues, organs, and parts of that individual other than the germ cells.

label: male primordial germ cell
definition: Cells coexpressing piwi-1 and nanos that are required for male gonad formation. Primordial germ cells are present in both asexual adults and sexual hermaphrodites. This term may be redundant with spermatogonial stem cell.

label: Category 2 cell
definition: Post-mitotic, mesenchymally located epidermal progenitors downstream of the zeta neoblasts.

label: acellular anatomical structure
definition: Anatomical structure that consists of cell parts and cell substances and together does not constitute a cell or a tissue.

label: meiotic telophase I
definition: The cell cycle phase which follows anaphase I of meiosis and during which the chromosomes arrive at the poles of the cell and the division of the cytoplasm starts.

label: enabled by
definition: inverse of enables

label: negative regulation of cellular metabolic process
definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways by which individual cells transform chemical substances.

label: embryonic wall
definition: The parenchymal space between the gut cavity and the primitive ectoderm containing undifferentiated blastomeres in Stage 3-5 embryos.

label: G2 phase neoblast
definition: neoblast undergoing mitotic G2 phase

label: positive regulation of biological process
definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of a biological process. Biological processes are regulated by many means; examples include the control of gene expression, protein modification or interaction with a protein or substrate molecule.

label: negative regulation of molecular function
definition: Any process that stops or reduces the rate or extent of a molecular function, an elemental biological activity occurring at the molecular level, such as catalysis or binding.

label: reproductive structure
definition: Any anatomical structure that is part of the reproductive system.

label: meiotic nuclear division
definition: One of the two nuclear divisions that occur as part of the meiotic cell cycle.

label: anatomical entity
definition: Biological entity that is either an individual member of a biological species or constitutes the structural organization of an individual member of a biological species.

label: anatomical entity
definition: Biological entity that is either an individual member of a biological species or constitutes the structural organization of an individual member of a biological species.

label: anatomical entity
definition: Biological entity that is either an individual member of a biological species or constitutes the structural organization of an individual member of a biological species.

label: embryonic pharynx
definition: An innervated, muscular pump that ingests yolk cells into the gut cavity. The embryonic pharynx is an extraembryonic tissue that forms during Stage 2, functions during Stages 3-5, and degenerates during Stages 6-7.

label: response to stimulus
definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus. The process begins with detection of the stimulus and ends with a change in state or activity or the cell or organism.

label: lumen
definition: The cavity or channel within a tube or tubular organ such as a blood vessel or the intestine.

label: acts upstream of, negative effect
definition: c 'acts upstream of, negative effect' p if c is enables f, and f is causally upstream of p, and the direction of f is negative

label: positive regulation of receptor binding
definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of a protein or other molecule binding to a receptor.

label: axon tract
definition: A group of axons linking two or more neuropils and having a common origin, termination

label: occurs in
definition: b occurs_in c =def b is a process and c is a material entity or immaterial entity& there exists a spatiotemporal region r and b occupies_spatiotemporal_region r.& forall(t) if b exists_at t then c exists_at t & there exist spatial regions s and s’ where & b spatially_projects_onto s at t& c is occupies_spatial_region s’ at t& s is a proper_continuant_part_of s’ at t

label: occurs in
definition: b occurs_in c =def b is a process and c is a material entity or immaterial entity& there exists a spatiotemporal region r and b occupies_spatiotemporal_region r.& forall(t) if b exists_at t then c exists_at t & there exist spatial regions s and s’ where & b spatially_projects_onto s at t& c is occupies_spatial_region s’ at t& s is a proper_continuant_part_of s’ at t

label: cephalic ganglia neuron
definition: A central nervous system neuron located within the planarian brain.

label: nucleolus
definition: A small, dense body one or more of which are present in the nucleus of eukaryotic cells. It is rich in RNA and protein, is not bounded by a limiting membrane, and is not seen during mitosis. Its prime function is the transcription of the nucleolar DNA into 45S ribosomal-precursor RNA, the processing of this RNA into 5.8S, 18S, and 28S components of ribosomal RNA, and the association of these components with 5S RNA and proteins synthesized outside the nucleolus. This association results in the formation of ribonucleoprotein precursors; these pass into the cytoplasm and mature into the 40S and 60S subunits of the ribosome.

label: dorsal epidermis cell
definition: cell which is part of the dorsal epidermis

label: brain visual center
definition: Region of the cephalic ganglia innervated by the optic nerve (posterior-projecting photoreceptor neuron fasiculated axons).

label: produces
definition: a produces b if some process that occurs_in a has_output b, where a and b are material entities. Examples: hybridoma cell line produces monoclonal antibody reagent; chondroblast produces avascular GAG-rich matrix.

label: capable of positively regulating
definition: Holds between c and p if and only if c is capable of some activity a, and a positively regulates p.

label: ventral side
definition: An anatomical region that is the entire part of an anatomical structure ventral to a horizontal plane and bounded on one side by the same horizontal plane.

label: embryo
definition: Anatomical entity that comprises the organism in the early stages of growth and differentiation that are characterized by cleavage, the laying down of fundamental tissues, and the formation of primitive organs and organ systems. For example, for mammals, the process would begin with zygote formation and end with birth. For insects, the process would begin at zygote formation and end with larval hatching. For plant zygotic embryos, this would be from zygote formation to the end of seed dormancy. For plant vegetative embryos, this would be from the initial determination of the cell or group of cells to form an embryo until the point when the embryo becomes independent of the parent plant.

label: pharynx musculature
definition: The total musculature within the pharynx.

label: zygote
definition: Diploid cell resulting from the fusion of male and female gametes at fertilization. [The_Dictionary_of_Cell_and_Molecular_Biology:Third_Edition ].

label: testis cell
definition: cell which is part of the testis

label: cellular response to stimulus
definition: Any process that results in a change in state or activity of a cell (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus. The process begins with detection of the stimulus by a cell and ends with a change in state or activity or the cell.

label: dorsal side
definition: An anatomical region that is the entire part of an anatomical structure dorsal to a horizontal plane and bounded on one side by the same transverse plane.

label: X1 cell
definition: A sorted cell population enriched for irradiation-sensitive, cycling cells (4n cells, with high levels of Hoescht 33342 staining) with scant cytoplasm (low levels of calcein-AM staining). X1 cells are enriched for cycling neoblasts.

label: proximal tubule epithelial cell
definition: Ciliated epithelial cells that assemble into proximal tubules.

label: negative regulation of cell cycle process
definition: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of a cellular process that is involved in the progression of biochemical and morphological phases and events that occur in a cell during successive cell replication or nuclear replication events.

label: regulation of cellular process
definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a cellular process, any of those that are carried out at the cellular level, but are not necessarily restricted to a single cell. For example, cell communication occurs among more than one cell, but occurs at the cellular level.

label: viscid gland cell
definition: A specialized insunk epithelial cell that is part of the adhesion glands which is responsible for production and excretion of the viscid substance allowing adherence to a substrate.

label: antero-dorsal region
definition: Anatomical region that overlaps the anterior and dorsal regions of a body or body part.

label: pharynx outer circular muscle cell
definition: Pharynx muscle fibers thar run circumferentially about the pharynx and lie just beneath the outer longitudinal pharynx muscles.

label: embryonic pharynx neuron
definition: A neuronal cell innervating the embryonic pharynx. Four neurons innervate the radial muscle fibers that ring the oral opening.

label: tertiary gut branch
definition: Gut branches originating from and connected to the secondary gut branches.

label: multicellular organismal process
definition: Any biological process, occurring at the level of a multicellular organism, pertinent to its function.

label: G1 phase germ cell cyst
definition: germ cell cyst undergoing mitotic G1 phase

label: sperm duct epithelial surface
definition: Epithelial surface lining the sperm duct.

label: oral-aboral axis
definition: An axis that extends from the oral opening to the furthest point in an organism that is directly opposite.

label: oral-aboral axis
definition: Axis that runs from the oral pole and to the aboral pole of the spherical embryo (Stage 3 through early Stage 6). The oral pole is centered around the embryonic pharynx; the aboral pole is located opposite the embryonic pharynx.

label: meiosis I cell cycle phase
definition: A meiotic cell cycle phase prior to a during which some part of meiosis I nuclear division or the proceeding cytokinesis occurs.

label: meiotic G2 phase
definition: The cell cycle 'gap' phase which is the interval between the completion of DNA synthesis and the beginning of DNA segregation by meiosis.

label: sagittal plane
definition: Anatomical plane which divides the body into right and left parts. This plane passes through the midline at the midline but does not always the midline.

label: sagittal plane
definition: Anatomical plane that divides a bilateral body into left and right parts, not necessarily of even size.

label: part of structure that is capable of
definition: this relation holds between c and p when c is part of some c', and c' is capable of p.

label: part of structure that is capable of
definition: this relation holds between c and p when c is part of some c', and c' is capable of p.

label: biological phase
definition: A distinct period or stage in a biological process or cycle.

label: regulation of response to stimulus
definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a response to a stimulus. Response to stimulus is a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus.

label: ectolecithal embryo
definition: Turbellarian (freshwater flatworm) embryos that undergo a modified form of cleavage due to separation of oocyte and yolk. Yolk is not contained within oocytes, and is produced by somatic vitellogenic gland cells.

label: tail tip
definition: The posterior-medial region of the tail margin.

label: negative regulation of phosphorus metabolic process
definition: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving phosphorus or compounds containing phosphorus.

label: wedge fragment
definition: A piece of tissue removed from the lateral margin at any given point that extendes interiorly to more medial structures.

label: embryonic gut cell surface
definition: The surface of phagocytic embryonic gut cells in contact with ingested yolk cells.

label: primary gut branch
definition: The largest branch of the triclad intestine. It is comprised of the gastrodermis, a columnar epithelium, surrounded by basal lamina and visceral musculature.

label: G2 phase oogonial cell
definition: oogonial cell undergoing mitotic G2 phase

label: life cycle stage
definition: A spatiotemporal region encompassing some part of the life cycle of an organism.

label: muscle progenitor cell
definition: Progenitor neoblasts implicated in the maintenance and regeneration of muscle fibers.

label: organ
definition: Anatomical structure that performs a specific function or group of functions.

label: positive regulation of phosphate metabolic process
definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving phosphates.

label: developmentally related to
definition: A relationship that holds between entities participating in some developmental process (GO:0032502)

label: pharynx longitudinal muscle cell
definition: Pharynx muscle fibers running anteroposterior (proximal to distal).

label: intercellular junction
definition: A cell junction that forms a connection between two or more cells in a multicellular organism; excludes direct cytoplasmic junctions such as ring canals.

label: existence starts during or after
definition: x existence starts during or after y if and only if the time point at which x starts is after or equivalent to the time point at which y starts. Formally: x existence starts during or after y iff α (x) >= α (y).

label: regulation of multicellular organismal process
definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a multicellular organismal process, the processes pertinent to the function of a multicellular organism above the cellular level; includes the integrated processes of tissues and organs.

label: postsynaptic cell
definition: A specialized area of membrane facing the presynaptic membrane on the tip of the nerve ending and separated from it by a minute cleft (the synaptic cleft). Neurotransmitters cross the synaptic cleft and transmit the signal to the postsynaptic membrane.

label: positive regulation of multi-organism process
definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of a multi-organism process, a process in which an organism has an effect on another organism of the same or different species.

label: ovary
definition: A gonad containing female germline stem cells which fuel oocyte production. Two ovaries are located ventally, underneath the body wall musculature, immediately posterior to the cephalic ganglia (brain) and adjacent to the ventral nerve cords. The neoblast compartment, including piwi-1+, nanos+ primordial germ cells, fuel formation of the ovaries during juvenile development.

label: zeta neoblast
definition: An abundant neoblast subclass consisting of p53+, zfp1+ progenitors required for maintenance and regeneration of epidermal cell type(s).

label: enteric neuron
definition: A neruon whose cell body is within an autonomic ganglion.

label: signaling receptor activator activity
definition: The function of interacting (directly or indirectly) with receptors such that the proportion of receptors in the active form is increased.

label: germline stem cell
definition: Stem cell that is the precursor of gametes.

label: nucleus
definition: A membrane-bounded organelle of eukaryotic cells in which chromosomes are housed and replicated. In most cells, the nucleus contains all of the cell's chromosomes except the organellar chromosomes, and is the site of RNA synthesis and processing. In some species, or in specialized cell types, RNA metabolism or DNA replication may be absent.

label: negative regulation of metabolic process
definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways within a cell or an organism.

label: auricle
definition: A sense organ located along the dorsolateral head margin. The auricular groove is highly innervtated by ciliated sensory neurons, and has an altered epidermis devoid of rhabdites and gland cells.

label: cellular_component
definition: A location, relative to cellular compartments and structures, occupied by a macromolecular machine when it carries out a molecular function. There are two ways in which the gene ontology describes locations of gene products: (1) relative to cellular structures (e.g., cytoplasmic side of plasma membrane) or compartments (e.g., mitochondrion), and (2) the stable macromolecular complexes of which they are parts (e.g., the ribosome).

label: obsolete extracellular region part
definition: OBSOLETE. Any constituent part of the extracellular region, the space external to the outermost structure of a cell. For cells without external protective or external encapsulating structures this refers to space outside of the plasma membrane. This term covers constituent parts of the host cell environment outside an intracellular parasite.

label: mitotic cell cycle process
definition: A process that is part of the mitotic cell cycle.

label: neuron associated cell (sensu Nematoda and Protostomia)
definition: Cells that are in close proximity to neurons.

label: acts upstream of or within
definition: c acts upstream of or within p if c is enables f, and f is causally upstream of or within p. c is a material entity and p is an process.

label: anterior to
definition: x anterior to y iff x is further along the antero-posterior axis than y, towards the head. An antero-posterior axis is an axis that extends through an organism from head end to opposite end of body or tail.

label: organelle membrane
definition: A membrane that is one of the two lipid bilayers of an organelle envelope or the outermost membrane of single membrane bound organelle.

label: adhesive papilla
definition: Finger-like processes at the terminal pore of adhesive gland cells around the marginal adhesive zone. They protrude past the epidermis and are longer microvilli, and shorter than cilia.

label: positive regulation of cell division
definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of cell division.

label: process
definition: An occurrent that has temporal proper parts and for some time t, p s-depends_on some material entity at t.

label: yolk cell
definition: An extraembryonic cell, produced by somatic vitellogenic glands in adult hermaphrodites, that provides nutrition to the developing embryo.

label: specific_to
definition: Restricted to domain

label: regulation of phosphorus metabolic process
definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving phosphorus or compounds containing phosphorus.

label: immediately causally upstream of
definition: p is immediately causally upstream of q iff both (a) p immediately precedes q and (b) p is causally upstream of q. In addition, the output of p  must be an input of q.

label: secondary gut branch
definition: Gut branches, originating from and connected to the primary gut branches, that extend laterally towards the body edge.

label: negative regulation of meiotic nuclear division
definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of meiosis.

label: intracellular granule
definition: Cytoplasmic part which forms a distinctive granular particle, which may or may not be visible using light microscopy.

label: has part structure that is capable of
definition: s 'has part structure that is capable of' p if and only if there exists some part x such that s 'has part' x and x 'capable of' p

label: anatomical side
definition: An anatomical region bounded by a plane perpendicular to an axis through the middle.

label: meiotic M phase
definition: A cell cycle phase during which nuclear division occurs, and which is comprises the phases: prophase, metaphase, anaphase and telophase and occurs as part of a meiotic cell cycle.

label: anatomical region
definition: A 3D region in space without well-defined compartmental boundaries; for example, the dorsal region of an ectoderm.

label: anatomical region
definition: A subdivision of an anatomical compartment.

label: extracellular organelle
definition: Organized structure of distinctive morphology and function, occurring outside the cell. Includes, for example, extracellular membrane vesicles (EMVs) and the cellulosomes of anaerobic bacteria and fungi.

label: extracellular organelle
definition: Organized structure of distinctive morphology and function, occurring outside the cell. Includes, for example, extracellular membrane vesicles (EMVs) and the cellulosomes of anaerobic bacteria and fungi.

label: regenerating anatomical structure
definition: An anatomical structure that is undergoing regeneration.

label: positive regulation of embryonic development
definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of embryonic development.

label: GABAergic neuron
definition: Neurons that express glutamine decarboxylase.

label: posterior fragment
definition: A fragment encompassing all or part of the posterior region of the animal.

label: organelle organization
definition: A process that is carried out at the cellular level which results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of an organelle within a cell. An organelle is an organized structure of distinctive morphology and function. Includes the nucleus, mitochondria, plastids, vacuoles, vesicles, ribosomes and the cytoskeleton. Excludes the plasma membrane.

label: posterior primary gut branch
definition: The primary gut branches of the triclad gut lateral and posterior to the pharynx and pharyngeal pouch.

label: anaphase spermatogonia
definition: spermatogonium undergoing mitotic anaphase

label: wedge wound
definition: A wound resulting from the removal of a piece of tissue from the lateral margin at any given point that extends interiorly to more medial structures.

label: dorsal surface
definition: Anatomical surface that located on the dorsal side of the body or body part.

label: anaphase
definition: The cell cycle phase, following metaphase, during which the chromosomes separate and migrate towards the poles of the spindle.

label: multicellular anatomical structure
definition: An anatomical structure that has more than one cell as a part.

label: round spermatid
definition: A cyst of 8 interconnected spermatocytes undergoes meiosis, producing 32 haploid round spermatids. Round spermatids express protein kinase A, andundergo morphogenesis to produce mature sperm.

label: embryo development
definition: The process whose specific outcome is the progression of an embryo from its formation until the end of its embryonic life stage. The end of the embryonic stage is organism-specific. For example, for mammals, the process would begin with zygote formation and end with birth. For insects, the process would begin at zygote formation and end with larval hatching. For plant zygotic embryos, this would be from zygote formation to the end of seed dormancy. For plant vegetative embryos, this would be from the initial determination of the cell or group of cells to form an embryo until the point when the embryo becomes independent of the parent plant.

label: collecting duct
definition: Non-ciliated tubules associated with the distal tubules, which cross the basement membrane and terminate in the dorsal epidermis.

label: trunk fragment
definition: A fragment derived from pre- and post-pharyngeal amputations, encompassing the pharynx and parapharyngeal region.

label: input of
definition: inverse of has input

label: input of
definition: inverse of has input

label: plug amputation
definition: An amputation of tissue, usually though the whole depth of the animal encompassing both dorsal and ventral sides, often made with a biopsy punch.

label: G1 phase spermatogonium
definition: spermatogonium undergoing mitotic G1 phase

label: basal surface
definition: Anatomical surface that is located on the basal side of the body or body part.

label: tail stripe
definition: Medial region of the tail; the parenchymal space between the posterior primary gut branches.

label: copulatory apparatus
definition: Accessory reproductive structures involved in copulation, egg capsule development and laying.

label: anterior primary gut branch
definition: The single, central gut branch of the triclad gut anterior to the pharynx.

label: anatomical point
definition: Non-material anatomical entity of zero dimension, which forms a boundary of an anatomical line or surface.

label: Stage 5
definition: A stage of Smed embryonic development defined by a unique gene expression signature and morphology, 5-7 days post-egg capsule deposition at 20˚C. Organogenesis onset. Downregulation of early embryo enriched transcripts and birth of adult lineages within the blastomere population. Early embryonic gut formation continues. Yolk ingestion into the gut cavity.

label: quality
definition: A dependent entity that inheres in a bearer by virtue of how the bearer is related to other entities

label: shape
definition: A morphological quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's ratios of distances between its features (points, edges, surfaces and also holes etc).

label: causal agent in process
definition: A relationship between a material entity and a process where the material entity has some causal role that influences the process

label: eumelanin
definition: The black pigment that gives non-neuronal pigment cells of the optic cup their characteristic color.

label: positive regulation of cell communication
definition: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of cell communication. Cell communication is the process that mediates interactions between a cell and its surroundings. Encompasses interactions such as signaling or attachment between one cell and another cell, between a cell and an extracellular matrix, or between a cell and any other aspect of its environment.

label: ipsilateral to
definition: On the same side as. For example, the left arm is ipsilateral to the left leg.

label: sensory neuron
definition: Any neuron having a sensory function; an afferent neuron conveying sensory impulses.

label: developmentally_contributes_to
definition: inverse of has developmental contribution from

label: developmentally contributes to
definition: inverse of has developmental contribution from

label: early male germ cell
definition: A premeiotic male germ cell (i.e., a spermatogonial stem cell or transit amplifying spermatogonial cell).

label: positive regulation of phosphorylation
definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of addition of phosphate groups to a molecule.

label: vacuole
definition: A closed structure, found only in eukaryotic cells, that is completely surrounded by unit membrane and contains liquid material. Cells contain one or several vacuoles, that may have different functions from each other. Vacuoles have a diverse array of functions. They can act as a storage organelle for nutrients or waste products, as a degradative compartment, as a cost-effective way of increasing cell size, and as a homeostatic regulator controlling both turgor pressure and pH of the cytosol.

label: obsolete has active participant
definition: x has participant y if and only if x realizes some active role that inheres in y

label: female primordial germ cell
definition: Cells expressing nanos that are located ventrally in the location that the ovaries form. Primordial germ cells are present in both asexual adults and sexual hermaphrodites. This term may be redundant with oogonial stem cell.

label: mitotic G2 phase
definition: The cell cycle 'gap' phase which is the interval between the completion of DNA synthesis and the beginning of DNA segregation by mitosis.

label: directly negatively regulates
definition: Process(P1) directly negatively regulates process(P2) iff: P1 negatively regulates P2 via direct physical interaction between an agent executing P1 (or some part of P1) and an agent executing P2 (or some part of P2).  For example, if protein A has protein binding activity(P1) that targets protein B and this binding  negatively regulates the kinase activity (P2) of protein B then P1 directly negatively regulates P2.

label: zygotene
definition: The cell cycle phase which follows leptotene during prophase I of meiosis, and during which each chromosome pairs with its homolog; the two become aligned and crossing over may occur.

label: organelle
definition: Organized structure of distinctive morphology and function. Includes the nucleus, mitochondria, plastids, vacuoles, vesicles, ribosomes and the cytoskeleton, and prokaryotic structures such as anammoxosomes and pirellulosomes. Excludes the plasma membrane.

label: organelle
definition: Organized structure of distinctive morphology and function. Includes the nucleus, mitochondria, plastids, vacuoles, vesicles, ribosomes and the cytoskeleton, and prokaryotic structures such as anammoxosomes and pirellulosomes. Excludes the plasma membrane.

label: lateral region
definition: Anatomical region laterally located on the body or body part.

label: cytoplasm
definition: All of the contents of a cell excluding the plasma membrane and nucleus, but including other subcellular structures

label: positively regulates
definition: Process(P1) postively regulates process(P2) iff: P1 initiates P2, or P1 increases the the frequency of initiation of P2 or the magnitude or rate of output of P2.

label: positively regulates
definition: Process(P1) postively regulates process(P2) iff: P1 initiates P2, or P1 increases the the frequency of initiation of P2 or the magnitude or rate of output of P2.

label: fragment
definition: A piece of tissue isolated from the body.

label: circular muscle progenitor cell
definition: piwi-1+, nkx1-1+ progenitor neoblasts required for specification of circular muscle fibers.

label: directly negatively regulated by
definition: Process(P2) is directly negatively regulated by process(P1) iff: P1 negatively regulates P2 via direct physical interaction between an agent executing P1 (or some part of P1) and an agent executing P2 (or some part of P2).  For example, if protein A has protein binding activity(P1) that targets protein B and this binding  negatively regulates the kinase activity (P2) of protein B then P2 directly negatively regulated by P1.

label: mitotic G1 phase
definition: The cell cycle 'gap' phase which is the interval between the completion of DNA segregation by mitosis and the beginning of DNA synthesis.

label: receptor ligand activity
definition: The activity of a gene product that interacts with a receptor to effect a change in the activity of the receptor. Ligands may be produced by the same, or different, cell that expresses the receptor. Ligands may diffuse extracellularly from their point of origin to the receiving cell, or remain attached to an adjacent cell surface (e.g. Notch ligands).

label: is direct form of
definition: relation p is the direct form of relation q iff p is a subPropertyOf q, p does not have the Transitive characteristic, q does have the Transitive characteristic, and for all x, y: x q y -> exists z1, z2, ..., zn such that x p z1 ... z2n y

label: nerve plexus
definition: Anatomical junction where subdivisions of two or more neural trees interconnect with one another to form a network through which nerve fibers of the constituent nerve trees become regrouped; together with other nerve plexuses, nerves and ganglia, it constitutes the peripheral nervous system. Examples: cervical nerve plexus, brachial nerve plexus, sacral nerve plexus[FMA].

label: has potential to developmentally contribute to
definition: x has potential to developmentrally contribute to y iff x developmentally contributes to y or x is capable of developmentally contributing to y

label: has potential to developmentally contribute to
definition: x has potential to developmentrally contribute to y iff x developmentally contributes to y or x is capable of developmentally contributing to y

label: has potential to developmentally contribute to
definition: x has potential to developmentrally contribute to y iff x developmentally contributes to y or x is capable of developmentally contributing to y

label: has potential to developmentally contribute to
definition: x has potential to developmentrally contribute to y iff x developmentally contributes to y or x is capable of developmentally contributing to y

label: G1 phase
definition: The cell cycle 'gap' phase which is the interval between the completion of DNA segregation (usually by mitosis or meiosis) and the beginning of DNA synthesis.

label: meiosis II stage spermatocyte
definition: spermatocyte undergoing meiosis II cell cycle phase

label: regulation of cellular component organization
definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a process involved in the formation, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cell structures, including the plasma membrane and any external encapsulating structures such as the cell wall and cell envelope.

label: position
definition: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's spatial location relative to other objects in the vicinity.

label: medial-lateral axis
definition: Axis that runs from the center of the body, starting at the anteroposterior axis and out to the lateral (left, right, dorsal or ventral) surface of the animal.

label: medial-lateral axis
definition: An axis that extends from the center of organism to one or other side.

label: optic cup
definition: A portion of the eye containing pigment cells and dendritic projections from photoreceptor neurons.

label: prophase  oogonial stem cell
definition: oogonial stem cell undergoing mitotic prophase

label: immediately superficial to
definition: x immediately superficial to y iff x superficial to y and x is contiguous with y.

label: immediately_superficial_to
definition: x immediately superficial to y iff x superficial to y and x is contiguous with y.

label: chromosomal_structural_element
definition: structural element of a chromosome, for example, a telomere and a centromere

label: regulation of protein binding
definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of protein binding.

label: positive regulation of reproductive process
definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of reproductive process.

label: sperm duct epithelium
definition: Ciliated epithelium lining the sperm duct.

label: head
definition: The head is the anterior-most division of the body [GO]. A three dimensional compartment bounded by the anterior margin or the head and the posterior boundary of the cephalic ganglia (brain).

label: male germ cell
definition: A male germ cell is a germ cell that supports male gamete production.

label: ventral midline
definition: The median line/ plane of bilateral symmetry along the anteroposterior axis on the ventral surface of the animal.

label: ovary lumen
definition: lumen which is part of the ovary

label: nuclear periphery
definition: The portion of the nuclear lumen proximal to the inner nuclear membrane.

label: intestinal phagocyte
definition: Absorptive digestive cells that engulf food particles for intracellular digestion.

label: anaphase spermatogonial stem cell
definition: spermatogonial stem cell undergoing mitotic anaphase

label: anatomical boundary
definition: A non-material anatomical entity of two dimensions. Anatomical boundaries are contiguous structures.

label: pharynx outer epithelium surface
definition: Epithelial surface covering the outside of the pharynx.

label: oogonial stem cell
definition: A piwi-1+, nanos+ cell residing in the ovary that self-renews and give rise to oogonial cells that differentiate into oocytes.

label: female germ cell
definition: Female germ cell is a germ cell that supports female gamete production.

label: epidermal progenitor cell
definition: Mitotically active zeta neoblasts and their post-mitotic descendants which undergo progressive differentiation and outward directed movement through the mesenchyme prior to incorporation into the epidermis, where terminal differentiation occurs.

label: non-ciliated epidermis
definition: Differentiating, immature epidermal cells lacking cilia.

label: negative regulation of cellular process
definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of a cellular process, any of those that are carried out at the cellular level, but are not necessarily restricted to a single cell. For example, cell communication occurs among more than one cell, but occurs at the cellular level.

label: efferent neuron
definition: A neuron which sends impulses peripherally to activate muscles or secretory cells.

label: cut
definition: A wound or cleft resulted from tissue separation into parts or laid open or penetrated with a sharp edge or instrument.

label: regulation of phosphate metabolic process
definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways involving phosphates.

label: overlaps
definition: x overlaps y iff they have some part in common.

label: overlaps
definition: x overlaps y if and only if there exists some z such that x has part z and z part of y

label: positive regulation of organelle organization
definition: Any process that increases the frequency, rate or extent of a process involved in the formation, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of an organelle.

label: neuron projection bundle
definition: A fasciculated bundle of neuron projections (GO:0043005), largely or completely lacking synapses.

label: metadata incomplete
definition: Class is being worked on; however, the metadata (including definition) are not complete or sufficiently clear to the branch editors.

label: molecularly interacts with
definition: An interaction relationship in which the two partners are molecular entities that directly physically interact with each other for example via a stable binding interaction or a brief interaction during which one modifies the other.

label: gonad primoridium
definition: This primordium develops into gonad

label: ommochrome pigment granule
definition: pigment granule which is part of the ommochrome pigment cell

label: chromosome
definition: A structure composed of a very long molecule of DNA and associated proteins (e.g. histones) that carries hereditary information.

label: cell junction
definition: A cellular component that forms a specialized region of connection between two or more cells or between a cell and the extracellular matrix. At a cell junction, anchoring proteins extend through the plasma membrane to link cytoskeletal proteins in one cell to cytoskeletal proteins in neighboring cells or to proteins in the extracellular matrix.

label: reproductive system
definition: Anatomical system that has as its parts the organs concerned with reproduction.

label: has ligand
definition: A relationship that holds between between a receptor and an chemical entity, typically a small molecule or peptide, that carries information between cells or compartments of a cell and which binds the receptor and regulates its effector function.

label: pax3/7+ neural progenitor cell
definition: piwi-1+, pax3/7+ progenitor neoblasts implicated in the production of DBH+ ventral midline neurons.

label: basophilic gland cell
definition: One of two distinct histochemical classes of gland cells, these are found near the ventral mesenchyme, the pharynx and in the dorsal region of the head. May also be called cyanophilic gland cells.

label: involved in or involved in regulation of
definition: c involved in or regulates p if and only if either (i) c is involved in p or (ii) c is involved in regulation of p

label: cephalic ganglia primordium
definition: This primordium develops into cephalic ganglia

label: pharynx neuron
definition: neuron which is part of the pharynx

label: regulation of cell cycle
definition: Any process that modulates the rate or extent of progression through the cell cycle.

label: apical region
definition: Anatomical region located on the apical end on the body or body part.

label: lysosome
definition: The digestive component of the cell. They are homogenous, dense, membrane bound organelles filled with acid hydrolases which break down polymers.

label: cell projection
definition: A prolongation or process extending from a cell.

label: gut branch
definition: The triclad planarian gut is serially bifrucated into connected lumens where each bifrucation is a branch.

label: stem cell
definition: A relatively undifferentiated cell that retains the ability to divide and proliferate throughout life to provide progenitor cells that can differentiate into specialized cells.

label: has negative regulatory component activity
definition: A relationship that holds between a GO molecular function and a component of that molecular function that negatively regulates the activity of the whole.  More formally, A 'has regulatory component activity' B iff :A and B are GO molecular functions (GO_0003674), A has_component B and A is negatively regulated by B.

label: serotonergic neural progenitor cell
definition: piwi-1+, lhx1/5-1+, pitx+ progenitor neoblasts required for specification of tph+ serotonergic neurons.

label: causally influences
definition: Holds between materal entities a and b if the activity of a is causally upstream of the activity of b, or causally upstream of a an activity that modifies b

label: octopaminergic neuron
definition: Neurons that express the biogenic amine octopamine.

label: integumental system
definition: Connected anatomical system that forms a barrier between an animal and its environment. In vertebrates, the integumental system consists of the epidermis, dermis plus associated glands and adnexa such as hair and scales. In invertebrates, the integumental system may include cuticle.

label: meiotic prophase I spermatocyte
definition: spermatocyte undergoing meiotic prophase I

label: positive regulation of signal transduction
definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of signal transduction.

label: endoplasmic reticulum
definition: Network of interconnected, flattened, and/or tubular membrane, known as cisternae. This membrane is contiguous with the outer nuclear membrane. The endoplasmic reticulum is involved in both protein and lipid synthesis.

label: gastrodermis
definition: The single cell layer columnar epithelial lining of the intestine. The gastrodermis is surrounded by a basal lamina and enteric muscle.

label: S phase spermatogonial stem cell
definition: spermatogonial stem cell undergoing mitotic S phase

label: orthogonal to
definition: crossing at right angles

label: post-blastema region
definition: Adjacent to blastema, or proximal to blastema.

label: embryonic pharynx circular muscle cell
definition: Differentiated muscle cell present in a circular muscle fiber of the embryonic pharynx.

label: anaphase germ cell cyst
definition: germ cell cyst undergoing mitotic anaphase

label: somatic gonadal cell
definition: A non-germline cell within the ovary or testis.

label: apical surface of the epidermis
definition: The apical surface of the single layered epidermis that is in contact with the environment.

label: material anatomical entity
definition: Anatomical entity that has mass.

label: material anatomical entity
definition: An anatomical entity that has mass.

label: material anatomical entity
definition: An anatomical entity that has mass.

label: spermatogonial stem cell
definition: gh4+, nanos+ cells residing at the testis periphery that self-renew and give rise to differentiating daughters that will ultimately produce haploid sperm.

label: primitive ectoderm
definition: A single cell layer of extraembryonic, post-mitotic ectodermal cells bounding the embryo. The primitive ectoderm forms during Stage 2 and is thought to degenerate as the definitive epidermis forms during Stages 5-7.

label: regulated by
definition: inverse of regulates

label: mucus
definition: A secreted, mucin-rich extracellular substance coating the epidermal surface of the animal implicated in gliding locomotion, substrate adhesion, innate immunity and predator avoidance.

label: positive regulation of cellular metabolic process
definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways by which individual cells transform chemical substances.

label: enteric musculature
definition: Visceral muscle surrounding the gut.

label: prophase neoblast
definition: neoblast undergoing mitotic prophase

label: negative regulation of biological process
definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of a biological process. Biological processes are regulated by many means; examples include the control of gene expression, protein modification or interaction with a protein or substrate molecule.

label: positive regulation of molecular function
definition: Any process that activates or increases the rate or extent of a molecular function, an elemental biological activity occurring at the molecular level, such as catalysis or binding.

label: rhabdome
definition: The light sensing structure consisting of photoreceptor neuron dendrites that project into the optic lumen and show close associations with eumelanin-containing pigment cup cells.

label: mitotic nuclear division
definition: A mitotic cell cycle process comprising the steps by which the nucleus of a eukaryotic cell divides; the process involves condensation of chromosomal DNA into a highly compacted form. Canonically, mitosis produces two daughter nuclei whose chromosome complement is identical to that of the mother cell.

label: pharynx lumen
definition: Anatomical space enclosed by the pharynx inner epithelium.

label: juvenile
definition: A sexually immature member of the Schmidtea mediterranea sexuallly reproducing biotype.

label: Smed asexual biotype
definition: Asexual animal strains that reproduce solely through fission followed by whole body regeneration. Asexual Smed are stable diploids that harbor a chromosome translocation, making them karyotypically distinct from sexual Smed.

label: asexual adult
definition: Asexually reproducing Schmidtea mediterranea exist as constitutive adults, undergoing successive cycles of fission and whole animal regeneration. Asexual Schmidtea mediterranea contain primordial germ cells, but do not possess a reproductive system.

label: marginal adhesive zone
definition: Zone present along the lateral dorsoventral boundary that sits just underneath the animal, in contact with substrates. It is comprised of bunches of adhesion gland cells whose terminal pores form pore rosettes through the dorsal ventral boundary epidermis.This region of is devoid of rhabdites.

label: electrically responsive cell
definition: A cell whose function is determined by its response to an electric signal.

label: contains process
definition: [copied from inverse property 'occurs in'] b occurs_in c =def b is a process and c is a material entity or immaterial entity& there exists a spatiotemporal region r and b occupies_spatiotemporal_region r.& forall(t) if b exists_at t then c exists_at t & there exist spatial regions s and s’ where & b spatially_projects_onto s at t& c is occupies_spatial_region s’ at t& s is a proper_continuant_part_of s’ at t

label: chemical amputation
definition: Amputation carried out by application of chemicals.

label: plane of autotomy
definition: An anatomical plane that bisects a zone of weakness in an appendage. When autotamy occurs, the appendage divides along this plane.

label: sexual reproduction
definition: A reproduction process that creates a new organism by combining the genetic material of two gametes, which may come from two organisms or from a single organism, in the case of self-fertilizing hermaphrodites, e.g. C. elegans, or self-fertilization in plants. It occurs both in eukaryotes and prokaryotes: in multicellular eukaryotic organisms, an individual is created anew; in prokaryotes, the initial cell has additional or transformed genetic material. In a process called genetic recombination, genetic material (DNA) originating from two gametes join up so that homologous sequences are aligned with each other, and this is followed by exchange of genetic information. After the new recombinant chromosome is formed, it is passed on to progeny.

label: enables subfunction
definition: Holds between an entity and an process P where the entity enables some larger compound process, and that larger process has-part P.

label: chromatin
definition: The ordered and organized complex of DNA, protein (histones), and sometimes RNA, that forms the chromosome.

label: causally downstream of or within
definition: inverse of causally upstream of or within

label: preceded by
definition: x is preceded by y if and only if the time point at which y ends is before or equivalent to the time point at which x starts. Formally: x preceded by y iff ω(y) <= α(x), where α is a function that maps a process to a start point, and ω is a function that maps a process to an end point.

label: preceded by
definition: X preceded_by Y iff: end(Y) before_or_simultaneous_with start(X)

label: preceded_by
definition: x is preceded by y if and only if the time point at which y ends is before or equivalent to the time point at which x starts. Formally: x preceded by y iff ω(y) <= α(x), where α is a function that maps a process to a start point, and ω is a function that maps a process to an end point.

label: preceded_by
definition: X preceded_by Y iff: end(Y) before_or_simultaneous_with start(X)

label: adhesion gland cell
definition: cell which is part of the adhesion gland

label: bulbar cavity
definition: An enlarged portion of the seminal vesicle, comprised of secretory epithelial cells, that connects to the ejaculatory duct within the penis papilla.

label: produced by
definition: a produced_by b iff some process that occurs_in b has_output a.

label: embryonic structure
definition: Anatomical structure that is part of an embryo.

label: TrpA+ neural progenitor cell
definition: piwi-1+, runt-1+, ap2+ progenitor neoblasts required for production of TrpA+ neurons.

label: pharynx inner nerve plexus
definition: Ring of the pharynx nerve plexus that is proximal to the lumen.

label: neuron
definition: The basic cellular unit of nervous tissue. Each neuron consists of a body, an axon, and dendrites. Their purpose is to receive, conduct, and transmit impulses in the nervous system.

label: ventral epidermis cell
definition: cell which is part of the ventral epidermis

label: plasma membrane
definition: The membrane surrounding a cell that separates the cell from its external environment. It consists of a phospholipid bilayer and associated proteins.

label: posterior to
definition: x posterior to y iff x is further along the antero-posterior axis than y, towards the body/tail. An antero-posterior axis is an axis that extends through an organism from head end to opposite end of body or tail.

label: posterior to
definition: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being located toward the rear of an organism relative to another entity.

label: specifically dependent continuant
definition: A continuant that inheres in or is borne by other entities. Every instance of A requires some specific instance of B which must always be the same.

label: releasing gland cell
definition: Specialized insunk epithelial cell that is part of the adhesion gland which is responsible for production of releasing substance.

label: antero-ventral region
definition: Anatomical region that overlaps the anterior and ventral regions of a body or body part.

label: pharynx inner circular muscle cell
definition: Pharynx muscle fiber that runs circumferentially about the pharynx and lies just beneath the inner logitudinal pharynx muscle fibers.

label: S phase germ cell cyst
definition: germ cell cyst undergoing mitotic S phase

label: developmental process
definition: A biological process whose specific outcome is the progression of an integrated living unit: an anatomical structure (which may be a subcellular structure, cell, tissue, or organ), or organism over time from an initial condition to a later condition.

label: positive regulation of mitotic nuclear division
definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of mitosis.

label: reproductive process
definition: A biological process that directly contributes to the process of producing new individuals by one or two organisms. The new individuals inherit some proportion of their genetic material from the parent or parents.

label: parenchyma
definition: A loosely organized collection of connective tissue and cells, including neoblasts and their immediate progeny, located in the space outside of the organs between the body wall musculature and the gut.

label: meiosis II cell cycle phase
definition: A meiotic cell cycle phase that occurs after meiosis I (the first meiotic nuclear division).

label: meiotic S phase
definition: The cell cycle phase, following G1, during which DNA synthesis takes place as part of a meiotic cell cycle.

label: positive regulation of response to stimulus
definition: Any process that activates, maintains or increases the rate of a response to a stimulus. Response to stimulus is a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus.

label: telomere
definition: The terminal region of a linear chromosome that includes the telomeric DNA repeats and associated proteins.

label: regulation of catalytic activity
definition: Any process that modulates the activity of an enzyme.

label: regulation of cell cycle process
definition: Any process that modulates a cellular process that is involved in the progression of biochemical and morphological phases and events that occur in a cell during successive cell replication or nuclear replication events.

label: anatomical cavity
definition: Anatomical space which contains portions of one or more body substances and is bounded by the internal surface of one maximally connected anatomical structure. Examples: cranial cavity, pharyngeal recess space, nasal cavity, tooth socket, cavity of serous sac, lumen of stomach, lumen of artery, fornix of vagina.

label: primitive gut
definition: Four large phagocytic cells associated with the embryonic pharynx.

label: prophase oogonial cell
definition: oogonial cell undergoing mitotic prophase

label: zygote stage
definition: A stage at which the organism is a single cell produced by means of sexual reproduction.

label: ventral surface
definition: Anatomical surface that is located on the ventral side of the body or body part.

label: phosphorylation
definition: The process of introducing a phosphate group into a molecule, usually with the formation of a phosphoric ester, a phosphoric anhydride or a phosphoric amide.

label: synapse
definition: The junction between a nerve fiber of one neuron and another neuron, muscle fiber or glial cell. As the nerve fiber approaches the synapse it enlarges into a specialized structure, the presynaptic nerve ending, which contains mitochondria and synaptic vesicles. At the tip of the nerve ending is the presynaptic membrane; facing it, and separated from it by a minute cleft (the synaptic cleft) is a specialized area of membrane on the receiving cell, known as the postsynaptic membrane. In response to the arrival of nerve impulses, the presynaptic nerve ending secretes molecules of neurotransmitters into the synaptic cleft. These diffuse across the cleft and transmit the signal to the postsynaptic membrane.

label: existence ends during or before
definition: x existence ends during or before y if and only if the time point at which x ends is before or equivalent to the time point at which y ends.

label: premeiotic germ cell
definition: A diploid germline stem cell or transit amplifying germ cell that has not committed to undergoing meiotic DNA replication, reductive divisions or terminal differentiation.

label: negative regulation of binding
definition: Any process that stops or reduces the rate or extent of binding, the selective interaction of a molecule with one or more specific sites on another molecule.

label: oviduct
definition: Ciliated tubes adjacent to the ventral nerve cords, adjoining the tuba and the bursal canal, that transport fertilized oocytes to the genital atrium.

label: non ciliated epithelial cell
definition: An epithelial cell lacking cilia.

label: cellular metabolic process
definition: The chemical reactions and pathways by which individual cells transform chemical substances.

label: parallel to
definition: x is parallel t y iff x and y are lines or planes which when extended indefinitely do not cross.

label: glycogen granule
definition: Cytoplasmic bead-like structures of animal cells, visible by electron microscope. Each granule is a functional unit with the biosynthesis and catabolism of glycogen being catalyzed by enzymes bound to the granule surface.

label: positive regulation of metabolic process
definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways within a cell or an organism.

label: axon
definition: The long process of a neuron that conducts nerve impulses, usually away from the cell body to the terminals and varicosities, which are sites of storage and release of neurotransmitter.

label: obsolete organelle part
definition: OBSOLETE. Any constituent part of an organelle, an organized structure of distinctive morphology and function. Includes constituent parts of the nucleus, mitochondria, plastids, vacuoles, vesicles, ribosomes and the cytoskeleton, but excludes the plasma membrane.

label: central nervous system neuron
definition: Any neuron that is part of a central nervous system.

label: flagellum
definition: Planarian undulipodia consisting of spermatazoa cell posterior protrusions. Planarian spermatozoa contain two flagella and are composed of 9 + 1 axonemal microtubule arrangements in their flagella (markedly different from the 9 + 2 structures generally observed in sperm of other animals).

label: process has causal agent
definition: Inverse of 'causal agent in process'

label: causally upstream of or within
definition: p 'causally upstream or within' q iff (1) the end of p is before the end of q and (2) the execution of p exerts some causal influence over the outputs of q; i.e. if p was abolished or the outputs of p were to be modified, this would necessarily affect q.

label: amputation
definition: A wound resulting in two or more separate tissue fragments.

label: negative regulation of cell division
definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of cell division.

label: activity directly positively regulates activity of
definition: Holds between molecular entities A and B where A can physically interact with B and in doing so positively regulates a process that B is capable of.  For example, A and B may be gene products and binding of B by A positively regulates the kinase activity of B.

label: membrane
definition: A lipid bilayer along with all the proteins and protein complexes embedded in it an attached to it.

label: positive regulation of meiotic nuclear division
definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of meiosis.

label: FACS sorted cell population
definition: Any number of cells from dissociated planarian tissue sorted via a FACS sorter for any parameter.

label: anterior region
definition: Compartment along the anteroposterior axis closer to the head rather than the tail, from the head margin to the esophagus.

label: anterior region
definition: Anatomical region anteriorly located on the body or body part.

label: nuclear division
definition: The division of a cell nucleus into two nuclei, with DNA and other nuclear contents distributed between the daughter nuclei.

label: mitotic anaphase
definition: The cell cycle phase during which chromosomes separate and migrate towards the poles of the spindle the as part of a mitotic cell cycle.

label: anterior side
definition: An anatomical region that is the entire part of an anatomical structure anterior to a transverse plane and bounded on one side by the same transverse plane.

label: meiotic interphase
definition: The cell cycle phase which begins after cytokinesis and ends when meiotic prophase begins. Meiotic cells have an interphase after each meiotic division, but only interphase I involves replication of the cell's DNA.

label: central nervous system
definition: The central nervous system is the core nervous system that serves an integrating and coordinating function. In vertebrates it consists of the neural tube derivatives: the brain and spinal cord. In invertebrates it includes central ganglia plus nerve cord.

label: transverse plane
definition: Anatomical plane that divides body into anterior and posterior parts.

label: lateral fragment
definition: A fragment derived from an amputation parallel to or along any edge, which overlaps the lateral region, dorso-lateral region, ventro-lateral region, antero-lateral margin, lateral margin, ventro-lateral margin, postero-lateral margin, dorso-lateral margin, antero-lateral region, postero-lateral region. [SMR: a fragment that encompasses the side of the animal, not necessarily longituduinal, or parallel to the midline]

label: longitudinal fragment
definition: a fragment derived from an amputation parallel to the midline.

label: primitive gut cell
definition: A phagocytic cell closely associated with the embryonic pharynx.

label: telophase spermatogonium
definition: spermatogonium undergoing mitotic telophase

label: regenerating fragment
definition: A fragment that has undergone wound healing and is undergoing tissue replacement and morphallaxis.

label: metaphase
definition: The cell cycle phase, following prophase or prometaphase in higher eukaryotes, during which chromosomes become aligned on the equatorial plate of the cell.

label: musculature system
definition: Total musculature of the planarian body.

label: elongate spermatid
definition: Spermatids expressing protein kinase A undergoing morphogenic changes to make mature sperm.

label: diagonal muscle cell
definition: Body wall muscle fibers arrayed diagonally along the anteroposterior axis.

label: regulation of multicellular organismal development
definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of multicellular organismal development.

label: defined class
definition: A defined class is a class that is defined by a set of logically necessary and sufficient conditions but is not a universal

label: cell communication
definition: Any process that mediates interactions between a cell and its surroundings. Encompasses interactions such as signaling or attachment between one cell and another cell, between a cell and an extracellular matrix, or between a cell and any other aspect of its environment.

label: immediately_deep_to
definition: This relation holds when both the deep_to and ajdacent_to relationship similarly hold.

label: immediately_deep_to
definition: x immediately deep to y iff x deep_to y and x is contiguous with y.

label: immediately deep to
definition: This relation holds when both the deep_to and ajdacent_to relationship similarly hold.

label: immediately deep to
definition: x immediately deep to y iff x deep_to y and x is contiguous with y.

label: anterior-posterior axis
definition: An axis that extends through an organism from head end to opposite end of body or tail.

label: anterior-posterior axis
definition: Axis that runs along the long axis of the animal from anterior (head) to posterior (tail). It is perpendicular to the dorsoventral axis and as such, it splits dorsal and ventral regions of the animal to either side.

label: anterior commissure
definition: A bundle of nerve fibers connecting the two cephalic ganglia.

label: tail fragment
definition: A fragment derived from a postpharyngeal amputation encompassing the tail.

label: testis somatic gonadal cell
definition: dmd-1+ expressing somatic cells within the testis that promote male GSC maintenance. dmd-1+, ophis-1+ somatic gonadal cells ensheath germ cells via long cytoplasmic processes and promote differentiation.

label: S phase spermatogonium
definition: spermatogonium undergoing mitotic S phase

label: spatially disjoint from
definition: A is spatially_disjoint_from B if and only if they have no parts in common

label: point incision
definition: A breach of the epidermis made with a defined edge or point.

label: peripheral nervous system
definition: A major division of the nervous system that contains nerves which connect the central nervous system (CNS) with sensory organs, other organs, muscles, blood vessels and glands.

label: kinase activity
definition: Catalysis of the transfer of a phosphate group, usually from ATP, to a substrate molecule.

label: embryonic subdivision
definition: Anatomical structure which is a subdivision of a whole developing/ embryonic organism, consisting of components of multiple anatomical systems.

label: copulatory bursa
definition: An organ that receives and stores sperm from mating partners.

label: dorsal ventral margin
definition: Region along the edge of the animal where the dorsal and ventral surfaces meet.

label: phagocytic cell
definition: A cell that engulfs large particles or cells via invagination of the plasma membrane and creation of a phagosome.

label: Stage 6
