definition: A stage of Smed embryonic development defined by a unique gene expression signature and morphology, 7 - 9 days post-egg capsule deposition at 20˚C. Organogenesis and morphogenesis. Definitive organ formation. Temporary embryonic cell types degenerate. Embryo elongation.

label: sympathetic neuron
definition: Sympathetic neurons are part of the sympathetic nervous system and are primarily adrenergic producing the neurotransmitter noradrenalin along with other neuropeptides.

label: causal relation between processes
definition: p is causally related to q if and only if p or any part of p and q or any part of q are linked by a chain of events where each event pair is one of direct activation or direct inhibition. p may be upstream, downstream, part of or a container of q.

label: excretory cell
definition: A cell involved in the elimination of metabolic and foreign toxins, and in maintaining the ionic, acid-base and water balance of biological fluids.

label: Stage 1
definition: A stage of Smed embryonic development, 0 - 2 days post-egg capsule deposition at 20˚C. Zygote and dispersed blastomere cleavage in a yolk syncytium.

label: negative regulation of cell communication
definition: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of cell communication. Cell communication is the process that mediates interactions between a cell and its surroundings. Encompasses interactions such as signaling or attachment between one cell and another cell, between a cell and an extracellular matrix, or between a cell and any other aspect of its environment.

label: motor neuron
definition: An efferent neuron that passes from the central nervous system or a ganglion toward or to a muscle and conducts an impulse that causes or inhibits movement.

label: embryonic gut
definition: A cryptic digestive cavity comprised of phagocytic embryonic gut cells.

label: signaling receptor activity
definition: Receiving a signal and transmitting it in the cell to initiate a change in cell activity. A signal is a physical entity or change in state that is used to transfer information in order to trigger a response.

label: whole organism
definition: Anatomical structure that is an individual member of of Schmidtea mediterranea or any other flatworm of the class Turbellaria.

label: anatomical junction
definition: An anatomical structure that connects two structures

label: cephalic ganglia progenitor cell
definition: A progenitor cell that gives rise to one or more of the cell type(s) in the nervous system.

label: pachytene
definition: The cell cycle phase which follows zygotene during prophase I of meiosis, and during which crossing over occurs between a chromatid in one partner and another chromatid in the homologous chromosome.

label: glial cell
definition: A non-neuronal cell of the nervous system. They not only provide physical support, but also respond to injury, regulate the ionic and chemical composition of the extracellular milieu, guide neuronal migration during development, and exchange metabolites with neurons.

label: causally downstream of
definition: inverse of upstream of

label: longitudinal region
definition: A region bounded by any sagittal plane though the animal and the left or right side of the animal. NOTE: sagittal plane is an anatomical plane that divides a bilateral body into left and right parts, not necessarily of even size

label: primordium
definition: Primordia are populations of contiguous cells that are morphologically distinct and already correspond in extent to a later organ/tissue.

label: directly positively regulated by
definition: Process(P2) is directly postively regulated by process(P1) iff: P1 positively regulates P2 via direct physical interaction between an agent executing P1 (or some part of P1) and an agent executing P2 (or some part of P2).  For example, if protein A has protein binding activity(P1) that targets protein B and this binding positively regulates the kinase activity (P2) of protein B then P2 is directly postively regulated by P1.

label: regulation of molecular function
definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a molecular function, an elemental biological activity occurring at the molecular level, such as catalysis or binding.

label: G2 phase
definition: The cell cycle 'gap' phase which is the interval between the completion of DNA synthesis and the beginning of DNA segregation (usually by mitosis or meiosis).

label: meiotic prophase II spermatocyte
definition: spermatocyte undergoing meiotic prophase II

label: negative regulation of cellular component organization
definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of a process involved in the formation, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cell structures, including the plasma membrane and any external encapsulating structures such as the cell wall and cell envelope.

label: continuant
definition: An entity that exists in full at any time in which it exists at all, persists through time while maintaining its identity and has no temporal parts.

label: proximal-distal axis
definition: Axis that starts at the distal part of an appendage, closest to the body, and runs to the proximal part of an appendage, farthest from the body.

label: proximal-distal axis
definition: An axis that extends from the point of attachment of a structure (proximal) to the  point furthest away from the plane of attachment (distal).

label: oral hemisphere
definition: Stage 3-5 embryo hemisphere centered around the embryonic pharynx.

label: metaphase oogonial stem cell
definition: oogonial stem cell undergoing mitotic metaphase

label: tuba lumen
definition: Anatomical space enclosed by tuba. Oocyte(s) are fertilized in the tuba lumen by sperm that traveled up the oviduct.

label: diakinesis stage spermatocyte
definition: spermatocyte undergoing diakinesis

label: prepharyngeal region
definition: Region of the juvenile or adult animal between the posterior end of the cephalic ganglia and the anterior end of the pharynx.

label: gamma neoblast
definition: An abundant neoblast subclass, exhibiting enriched expression of gata456a, hnf4, prox-1 and nkx2.2, implicated in maintenance and regeneration of the definitive gut.

label: flame cell lumen
definition: lumen which is part of the flame cell

label: ommochrome pigment cell
definition: Parenchymal cells that synthesize and contain brown ommonchrome pigment.

label: longitudinal muscle cell
definition: Body wall muscle fibers arrayed along the anteroposterior axis. Upon regeneration, these muscles are thought to be established from truncated pre-existing fibers.Inner most body wall muscle fibers arrayed along the anteroposterior axis. These fibers are thicker than the outer longitudinal muscle fibers. The pattern of these muscles differs along the dorsoventral axis, with the dorsal arrangement converging at the central zone of the anterior pole. The ventral arrangement is more parallel or may diverge slightly as it approaches the ventral pole.

label: telophase spermatogonial stem cell
definition: spermatogonial stem cell undergoing mitotic telophase

label: phosphorus metabolic process
definition: The chemical reactions and pathways involving the nonmetallic element phosphorus or compounds that contain phosphorus, usually in the form of a phosphate group (PO4).

label: pharynx pouch epithelial surface
definition: The surface of the parapharyngeal pouch facing the pharynx.

label: cement gland
definition: Glands surrounding the genital atrium that are required for production of the proteinaceous egg capsule shell and stalk.

label: epidermis
definition: A single cell layer of post-mitotic epithelial cells containing ciliated and non-ciliated cell types forming the exterior surface of the animal.

label: has part that occurs in
definition: p has part that occurs in c if and only if there exists some p1, such that p has_part p1, and p1 occurs in c.

label: nuclear envelope
definition: The double lipid bilayer enclosing the nucleus and separating its contents from the rest of the cytoplasm; includes the intermembrane space, a gap of width 20-40 nm (also called the perinuclear space).

label: excitatory motor neuron
definition: A motor neuron that is capable of directly inducing muscle contraction.

label: dendrite
definition: A neuron projection that has a short, tapering, morphology. Dendrites receive and integrate signals from other neurons or from sensory stimuli, and conduct nerve impulses towards the axon or the cell body. In most neurons, the impulse is conveyed from dendrites to axon via the cell body, but in some types of unipolar neuron, the impulse does not travel via the cell body.

label: multicellular organism development
definition: The biological process whose specific outcome is the progression of a multicellular organism over time from an initial condition (e.g. a zygote or a young adult) to a later condition (e.g. a multicellular animal or an aged adult).

label: negative regulation of organelle organization
definition: Any process that decreases the frequency, rate or extent of a process involved in the formation, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of an organelle.

label: triangular
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's having three angles.

label: uncurated
definition: Nothing done yet beyond assigning a unique class ID and proposing a preferred term.

label: parenchymal cell
definition: cell which is part of the parenchyma

label: chromosome arm
definition: Under the microscope chromosomes appear as thin, thread-like structures. They all have a short arm and long arm separated by a primary constriction called the centromere. The short arm is designated as p and the long arm as q.

label: dorsal region
definition: Three dimensional compartment along the dorsoventral axis that is above the anteroposterior axis, containing the eyes.

label: dorsal region
definition: Anatomical region dorsally located on the body or body part.

label: cell-cell junction
definition: A cell junction that forms a connection between two or more cells in a multicellular organism; excludes direct cytoplasmic junctions such as ring canals.

label: oviduct epithelial cell
definition: Ciliated epithelial cells that assemble into the oviduct.

label: embryonic pharynx lumen
definition: A lumen enclosed by the embryonic pharynx epithelial cells through which yolk cells are transported into the embryonic gut cavity.

label: is active in
definition: c executes activity in d if and only if c enables p and p occurs_in d.  Assuming no action at a distance by gene products, if a gene product enables (is capable of) a process that occurs in some structure, it must have at least some part in that structure.

label: eye primordium
definition: This primordium develops into eye

label: pharynx epithelial cell
definition: epithelial cell which is part of the pharynx

label: basal region
definition: Anatomical region located basally on the body or body part.

label: positive regulation of transferase activity
definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of transferase activity, the catalysis of the transfer of a group, e.g. a methyl group, glycosyl group, acyl group, phosphorus-containing, or other groups, from a donor compound to an acceptor.

label: actin-based cell projection
definition: A cell projection supported by an assembly of actin filaments.

label: gamete
definition: A mature sexual reproductive cell having a single set of unpaired chromosomes.

label: has positive regulatory component activity
definition: A relationship that holds between a GO molecular function and a component of that molecular function that positively regulates the activity of the whole.  More formally, A 'has regulatory component activity' B iff :A and B are GO molecular functions (GO_0003674), A has_component B and A is positively regulated by B.

label: klf+ sensory neuron progenitor cell
definition: piwi-1+, klf+ progenitor neoblasts required for production of cintillo+ sensory neurons.

label: secretory system
definition: Anatomical system that has as its parts cells and glands devoted to the discharge of substances such as mucus.

label: leptotene stage spermatocyte
definition: spermatocyte undergoing leptotene

label: negative regulation of signal transduction
definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of signal transduction.

label: negative regulation of signaling receptor activity
definition: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of a signaling receptor activity.

label: rough endoplasmic reticulum
definition: Network of interconnected, flattened, and/or tubular membrane, known as cisternae. This membrane is contiguous with the outer nuclear membrane. The endoplasmic reticulum is involved in both protein and lipid synthesis.

label: goblet cell
definition: Secretory cells that release digestive enzymes into the lumen of the intestine.

label: G2 phase spermatogonial stem cell
definition: spermatogonial stem cell undergoing mitotic G2 phase

label: passes through
definition: Intersects at two points.

label: specialized neoblast
definition: A presumptive progenitor cell that expresses both pan-neoblast markers and pro-differentiation gene(s), frequently developmental transcription factors, implicated in lineage commitment and tissue-specific differentiation programs.

label: telophase germ cell cyst
definition: germ cell cyst undergoing mitotic telophase

label: immaterial anatomical entity
definition: Anatomical entity that has no mass.

label: immaterial anatomical entity
definition: An anatomical entity that has no mass.

label: meiotic prophase II
definition: The cell cycle phase which is the first stage of meiosis II and during which chromosomes condense and the two daughter centrioles and their asters migrate toward the poles of the cell.

label: negatively regulated by
definition: inverse of negatively regulates

label: esophagus
definition: Attachment between the triclad gut and the proximal end of the pharynx.

label: metaphase neoblast
definition: neoblast undergoing mitotic metaphase

label: X1(FS) cell
definition: A heterogeneous sorted cell population of unstained planarian cells with similar size and complexity to irradiation-sensitive, cycling cells contained in the X1 gate. Unlike X1 cells, X1(FS) cells are amenable to cell transplantation.

label: embryonic pharynx radial muscle cell
definition: Differentiated radial muscle cell present in the embryonic pharynx.

label: rhabdomere
definition: The dendritic process of a bipolar photoreceptor neuron that projects into the optic cup lumen and senses light.

label: digestive tract lumen
definition: An anatomical space that is surrounded by a digestive tract.

label: reproductive system product
definition: Products of the reproductive system include gametes, zygotes, yolk cells and egg capsules.

label: nervous system
definition: The nervous system is an organ system containing predominantly neuron and glial cells. In bilaterally symmetrical organisms, it is arranged in a network of tree-like structures connected to a central body. The main functions of the nervous system are to regulate and control body functions, and to receive sensory input, process this information, and generate behavior [CUMBO].

label: mechanosensory neuron
definition: Any neuron that is capable of some detection of mechanical stimulus involved in sensory perception.

label: chemical pharynx amputation
definition: Amputation of the phaynx, including the esophagus, by treatment with Sodium Azide.

label: protonephridia
definition: Excretory organs consisting of flame cells, proximal tubules, and distal tubules connected to a mesenchymal collecting duct.

label: linear amputation
definition: An amputation performed with a transverse, oblique or longitudinal cut.

label: positive regulation of multicellular organismal process
definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of an organismal process, any of the processes pertinent to the function of an organism above the cellular level; includes the integrated processes of tissues and organs.

label: heterochromatin
definition: A compact and highly condensed form of chromatin.

label: definition
definition: The official definition, explaining the meaning of a class or property. Shall be Aristotelian, formalized and normalized. Can be augmented with colloquial definitions.

label: definition
definition: The official definition, explaining the meaning of a class or property. Shall be Aristotelian, formalized and normalized. Can be augmented with colloquial definitions.

label: involved in regulation of
definition: c involved in regulation of p if c is involved in some p' and p' regulates some p

label: precedes
definition: x precedes y if and only if the time point at which x ends is before or equivalent to the time point at which y starts. Formally: x precedes y iff ω(x) <= α(y), where α is a function that maps a process to a start point, and ω is a function that maps a process to an end point.

label: pigmentation
definition: The accumulation of pigment in an organism, tissue or cell, either by increased deposition or by increased number of cells.

label: body wall muscle cell
definition: cell which is part of the body wall musculature

label: Category 1 cell
definition: Irradiation-sensitive, mesenchymal cells that are absent from the head region anterior to the eyes and the pharynx. The Category 1 designation encompasses the neoblast population.

label: collecting duct epithelial cell
definition: Nonciliated epithelial cells that assemble into collecting ducts.

label: anterior pole progenitor cell
definition: piwi-1+, foxD+, prep+ progenitor neoblasts required for formation of the anterior pole.

label: secretory vesicle
definition: A cytoplasmic, membrane bound vesicle that is capable of fusing to the plasma membrane to release its contents into the extracellular space.

label: has input
definition: p has input c iff: p is a process, c is a material entity, c is a participant in p, c is present at the start of p, and the state of c is modified during p.

label: visual system cell
definition: cell which is part of the visual system

label: causal relation between material entity and a process
definition: A relationship that holds between a material entity and a process in which causality is involved, with either the material entity or some part of the material entity exerting some influence over the process, or the process influencing some aspect of the material entity.

label: regulation of transferase activity
definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of transferase activity, the catalysis of the transfer of a group, e.g. a methyl group, glycosyl group, acyl group, phosphorus-containing, or other groups, from one compound (generally regarded as the donor) to another compound (generally regarded as the acceptor). Transferase is the systematic name for any enzyme of EC class 2.

label: tissue
definition: Multicellular anatomical structure that consists of many cells of one or a few types, arranged in an extracellular matrix such that their long-range organisation is at least partly a repetition of their short-range organisation.

label: postero-lateral region
definition: Anatomical region that overlaps the posterior and lateral regions of the body or body part.

label: pharynx inner longitudinal muscle cell
definition: Pharynx muscle fibers running anteroposterior which lie beneath both the inner circular muscle fibers and the apical, ciliated portion of the epithium lining the lumenal surface.

label: trail cell
definition: Ovo+ neoblasts and post-mitotic eye progenitors that simultaneously migrate and differentiate into photoreceptor neurons and non-neuronal pigment cup cells comprising the optic cup.

label: G2 phase germ cell cyst
definition: germ cell cyst undergoing mitotic G2 phase

label: negative regulation of fertilization
definition: Any process that decreases the rate, frequency or extent of fertilization. Fertilization is the union of gametes of opposite sexes during the process of sexual reproduction to form a zygote. It involves the fusion of the gametic nuclei (karyogamy) and cytoplasm (plasmogamy).

label: negative regulation of response to stimulus
definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of a response to a stimulus. Response to stimulus is a change in state or activity of a cell or an organism (in terms of movement, secretion, enzyme production, gene expression, etc.) as a result of a stimulus.

label: embryonic digestive system
definition: A cryptic digestive system in Stage 3-6 embryos comprised of temporary embryonic cell types and organs, including the embryonic pharynx and primitive gut cells. Embryonic gut cells, likely produced from blastomeres, form a phagocytic tissue layer surrounding the inner gut cavity during Stages 4-6. It is not known whether the embryonic gut is temporary embryonic tissue or a definitive tissue. For convenience, the embryonic gut is currently designated as an extraembryonic structure because cell type specific markers for the embryonic gut do not stain the definitive gut in hatchlings or adult animals.

label: tight junction
definition: A cell-cell junction that seals cells together in an epithelium in a way that prevents even small molecules from leaking from one side of the sheet to the other.

label: neuropil
definition: A cluster of neurites that is part of a nervous system and forms a network of dendrites and axons where synapses are present and in which neuronal somata do not occur.

label: embryonic pharynx lumen epithelial surface
definition: The epithelial cell surface lining the embryonic pharynx lumen.

label: negative regulation of cell cycle
definition: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the rate or extent of progression through the cell cycle.

label: sperm
definition: A mature male germ cell that develops from a spermatid.

label: quarternary gut branch
definition: Gut branches originating from and connected to the tertiary gut branches.

label: metaphase oogonial cell
definition: oogonial cell undergoing mitotic metaphase

label: external_definition
definition: An alternate textual definition for a class taken unmodified from an external source. This definition may have been used to derive a generalized definition for the new class.

label: distal tubule
definition: Sinusoidal, non-ciliated tubules connected to proximal tubules within the parenchyma. Tubules are formed via intercellular junctions between two epithelial cells.

label: synaptic cleft
definition: The narrow gap that separates the presynaptic and postsynaptic membranes, into which neurotransmitter is released.

label: regulation of meiotic nuclear division
definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of meiotic nuclear division, the process in which the nucleus of a diploid cell divides twice forming four haploid cells, one or more of which usually function as gametes.

label: presynaptic cell
definition: The part of a synapse that is part of the presynaptic cell.

label: penis papilla
definition: A rounded protuberance, connected to the seminal vesicles, responsible for transferring semen into a mating partner's bursal canal.

label: pharynx
definition: A plicate and protrusible organ that is the sole point of entry and exit for the Triclad gut. It contains epithelial, muscular, secretory and neuronal cell types.

label: anatomical space
definition: Non-material anatomical entity of three dimensions, that is generated by morphogenetic or other physiologic processes; is surrounded by one or more anatomical structures; contains one or more organism substances or anatomical structures.

label: overlaps
definition: x overlaps y iff they have some part in common.

label: overlaps
definition: x overlaps y if and only if there exists some z such that x has part z and z part of y

label: incision
definition: A breach of the epidermis made with a defined edge or point.

label: extracellular regulation of signal transduction
definition: Any regulation of signal transduction that takes place in the extracellular region.

label: bursal canal
definition: The passageway connecting the genital atrium to the copulatory bursa. Part of the copulatory apparatus. During mating, sperm from a partner is deposited into the bursal canal, where it collects in the copulatory bursa before travelling up the oviducts to the tuba.

label: protonephridial progenitor cell
definition: Neoblasts and post-mitotic, differentiating daughters coexpressing POU2-3, six1/2-2, Sal1, Eya and Osr,required for maintenance and regeneration of protonephridial cell types.

label: axoneme
definition: The bundle of microtubules and associated proteins that forms the core of cilia (also called flagella) in eukaryotic cells and is responsible for their movements.

label: derives from
definition: a relation between two distinct material entities, the new entity and the old entity, in which the new entity begins to exist when the old entity ceases to exist, and the new entity inherits the significant portion of the matter of the old entity

label: regulation of fertilization
definition: Any process that modulates the rate, frequency or extent of fertilization. Fertilization is the union of gametes of opposite sexes during the process of sexual reproduction to form a zygote. It involves the fusion of the gametic nuclei (karyogamy) and cytoplasm (plasmogamy).

label: gap junction
definition: A cell-cell junction composed of pannexins or innexins and connexins, two different families of channel-forming proteins.

label: dorsal to
definition: x dorsal to y iff x is further along the dorso-ventral axis than y, towards the back. A dorso-ventral axis is an axis that extends through an organism from back (e.g. spinal column) to front (e.g. belly).

label: membrane-bounded organelle
definition: Organized structure of distinctive morphology and function, bounded by a single or double lipid bilayer membrane. Includes the nucleus, mitochondria, plastids, vacuoles, and vesicles. Excludes the plasma membrane.

label: anterior gut branch
definition: A branch of the triclad gut located anterior to the pharynx.

label: regulation of nuclear division
definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of nuclear division, the partitioning of the nucleus and its genetic information.

label: realizable entity
definition: A specifically dependent continuant  that inheres in continuant  entities and are not exhibited in full at every time in which it inheres in an entity or group of entities. The exhibition or actualization of a realizable entity is a particular manifestation, functioning or process that occurs under certain circumstances.

label: adhesion gland
definition: Groupings of specialized epithelial cells located along the dorsal ventral margin. Adhesion glands are comprised of three cell types, the viscid and releasing gland cells which penetrate through an epithelial anchor cell and terminate at the epidermal surface.

label: bounding membrane of organelle
definition: Examples include the outer membranes of double membrane bound organelles such as mitochondria as well as the bounding membranes of single-membrane bound organelles such as lysosomes.

label: derived cell population
definition: Cells isolated from dissociated planarian tissue.

label: cellular anatomical entity
definition: A part of a cellular organism that is either an immaterial entity or a material entity with granularity above the level of a protein complex but below that of an anatomical system. Or, a substance produced by a cellular organism with granularity above the level of a protein complex.

label: posterior side
definition: An anatomical region that is the entire part of an anatomical structure posterior to a transverse plane and bounded on one side by the same transverse plane.

label: mitotic interphase
definition: The cell cycle phase following cytokinesis which begins with G1 phase, proceeds through S phase and G2 phase and ends when mitotic prophase begins. During interphase the cell readies itself for mitosis and the replication of its DNA occurs.

label: cellular process
definition: Any process that is carried out at the cellular level, but not necessarily restricted to a single cell. For example, cell communication occurs among more than one cell, but occurs at the cellular level.

label: rhabdite
definition: Straight or curved rod-like structures within the epidermal cells, oriented with long axis at right angles to the epidermal surface, that are discharged into mucous secretions.

label: developmental process involved in reproduction
definition: A developmental process in which a progressive change in the state of some part of an organism specifically contributes to its ability to form offspring.

label: horizontal plane
definition: Anatomical plane that divides bilateral body into dorsal and ventral parts.

label: subepidermal nerve plexus
definition: Plexus of nerves located just between the epidermis and the body wall musculature.

label: G1 phase oogonial cell
definition: oogonial cell undergoing mitotic G1 phase

label: longitudinal orientation
definition: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is directed along the longitudinal or anterior-posterior axis.

label: sagittal orientation
definition: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is in the sagittal plane. This plane runs longitudinally and is not necessarily medial.

label: physical quality
definition: A quality of a physical entity that exists through action of continuants at the physical level of organisation in relation to other entities.

label: multi-organism process
definition: A biological process which involves another organism of the same or different species.

label: is a defining property chain axiom
definition: If R <- P o Q is a defining property chain axiom, then it also holds that R -> P o Q. Note that this cannot be expressed directly in OWL

label: prophase
definition: The cell cycle phase which is the first stage of M phase of meiosis and mitosis and during which chromosomes condense and the two daughter centrioles and their asters migrate toward the poles of the cell.

label: neoblast
definition: A heterogeneous population of pluripotent, somatic adult stem cells and lineage primed progenitors that are required for maintenance and regeneration of all cell types in planaria, including the germline.

label: oogonial cell
definition: An undifferentiated germ cell that proliferates rapidly and gives rise to oocytes.

label: digestive system
definition: Anatomical system that has as its parts the organs devoted to the ingestion, digestion, and assimilation of food and the discharge of residual wastes.

label: named class expression
definition: A named class expression is a logical expression that is given a name. The name can be used in place of the expression.

label: apical-basal axis relative to substrate
definition: An axis that extends through an organism or organism part from the part of the organism or organism part attached to a substrate (basal) to the furthest from the attachment (apical). Note that the apical-basal axis is often used for organismal parts where there is attachment via a basal lamina or other structure.

label: lateral branch
definition: Nerve branches that extend from the lateral side of each cephalic ganglia lobe. Each lobe has nine lateral branches which terminate in sensory organs. Evidence suggests they play a role in chemosensation.

label: prepharyngeal fragment
definition: A fragment derived from two prepharyngeal amputations, removing the head and posterior regions of the animal.

label: ovarian somatic gonadal cell
definition: ophis+ somatic cells (gh4-, nanos-) in the ovary that may provide trophic support to female germline stem cells and differentiating oogonia.

label: pharynx pouch
definition: An epithelial structure housing the pharynx, connected to the esophagus and mouth.

label: pore
definition: An anatomical space that is an opening, usually at the end of a canal or duct, on the surface of the integument or the lining of an internal anatomical space.

label: G2 phase spermatogonium
definition: spermatogonium undergoing mitotic G2 phase

label: negative regulation of protein binding
definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of protein binding.

label: seminal vesicle
definition: Glandular pouches adjoining the sperm ducts which produce seminal fluid.

label: cephalic ganglia
definition: The planarian brain, consisting of two bilaterally symmetric lobes occupying a ventral position in the head.

label: pharynx tip
definition: The distal-most end of the pharnyx containing an opening to the pharynx lumen.

label: Stage 7
definition: A stage of Smed embryonic development defined by a unique gene expression signature and morphology, 9 - 11 days post-egg capsule deposition at 20˚C. Organogenesis and organ maturation continues. Embryos elongated. Eyes just visible. Onset of gliding motility.

label: anterior surface
definition: Anatomical surface that is located on the anterior side of the body or body part.

label: unipolar neuron
definition: Neuron with one neurite that extends from the cell body.

label: extracellular matrix
definition: A structure lying external to one or more cells, which provides structural support, biochemical or biomechanical cues for cells or tissues.

label: Stage 2
definition: A stage of Smed embryonic development defined by a unique gene expression signature and morphology, 2 - 3 days post-egg capsule deposition at 20˚C. Sphere formation. A fraction of the blastomeres differentiate into temporary embryonic tissues that provide form and function to the embryo. Undifferentiated blastomeres remain in the embryonic wall.

label: deep_to
definition: Further away from the surface of the organism. Thus, the muscular layer is deep to the skin, but superficial to the intestines.

label: deep to
definition: Further away from the surface of the organism. Thus, the muscular layer is deep to the skin, but superficial to the intestines.

label: epidermal cell
definition: An epithelial cell of the integument (the outer layer of an organism).

label: regeneration
definition: The regrowth of a lost or destroyed body part, such as an organ or tissue. This process may occur via renewal, repair, and/or growth alone (i.e. increase in size or mass).

label: mitotic M phase
definition: A cell cycle phase during which nuclear division occurs, and which is comprises the phases: prophase, metaphase, anaphase and telophase and occurs as part of a mitotic cell cycle.

label: cell
definition: A material entity of anatomical origin (part of or deriving from an organism) that has as its parts a maximally connected cell compartment surrounded by a plasma membrane.

label: ventral to
definition: x ventral to y iff x is further along the dorso-ventral axis than y, towards the front. A dorso-ventral axis is an axis that extends through an organism from back (e.g. spinal column) to front (e.g. belly).

label: dorsal epidermis progenitor cell
definition: A progenitor cell that gives rise to one or more of the cell type(s) in the dorsal epidermis.

label: ventral region
definition: Compartment along the dorsoventral axis that is below the anteroposterior axis.

label: ventral region
definition: Anatomical region ventrally located on the body or body part.

label: ganglion
definition: A biological tissue mass of nerve cell bodies.

label: material entity
definition: An independent continuant that is spatially extended whose identity is independent of that of other entities and can be maintained through time.

label: capable of
definition: A relation between a material entity (such as a cell) and a process, in which the material entity has the ability to carry out the process.

label: capable of
definition: A relation between a material entity (such as a cell) and a process, in which the material entity has the ability to carry out the process.

label: has effector activity
definition: A 'has effector activity' B if A and B are GO molecular functions (GO_0003674),  A 'has component activity' B and B is the effector (output function) of B.  Each compound function has only one effector activity.

label: brain commissure
definition: any of the nerve fiber tracts that span the longitudinal fissure between the cerebral and/or cerebellar hemispheres of the brain

label: has potential to develop into
definition: x has the potential to develop into y iff x develops into y or if x is capable of developing into y

label: has potential to develop into
definition: x has the potential to develop into y iff x develops into y or if x is capable of developing into y

label: has potential to develop into
definition: x has the potential to develop into y iff x develops into y or if x is capable of developing into y

label: has potential to develop into
definition: x has the potential to develop into y iff x develops into y or if x is capable of developing into y

label: meiotic metaphase 2 spermatocyte
definition: spermatocyte undergoing meiotic metaphase II

label: occurrent
definition: An entity that has temporal parts and that happens, unfolds or develops through time.

label: anterior pole
definition: Distinct anterior cluster of muscle cells located at the midline which express notum, follistatin, zic-1, and foxD.

label: anaphase oogonial stem cell
definition: oogonial stem cell undergoing mitotic anaphase

label: thick fragment
definition: A longitudinal fragment containing the preexisting midline and medial structures.

label: regulation of embryonic development
definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of embryonic development.

label: meiotic metaphase 1 stage spermatocyte
definition: spermatocyte undergoing meiotic metaphase I

label: imported from
definition: For external terms/classes, the ontology from which the term was imported

label: anatomical surface
definition: A 2D surface of an anatomical continuant.

label: mouth
definition: The sole point of entry and exit for the Triclad planarian flatworm gut. The mouth is connected to the pharyngeal pouch to allow for exit and re-entry of the pharynx on the ventral side of the animal. The mouth contains several cell types, including epithelial cells, muscle, and secretory cells.

label: G1 phase oogonial stem cell
definition: oogonial stem cell undergoing mitotic G1 phase

label: extraembryonic organ
definition: Organ that is associated with an embryo and derived from the zygote from which it develops, but which does not contribute to the embryo proper or to structures that are part of the same organism after embryogenesis.

label: reproduction
definition: The production of new individuals that contain some portion of genetic material inherited from one or more parent organisms.

label: oviduct lumen
definition: Anatomical space enclosed by the oviduct epithelium.

label: Category 3 cell
definition: Post-mitotic, mesenchymally located epidermal progenitors downstream of the Category 2 cells.

label: nuclear inner membrane
definition: The inner, i.e. lumen-facing, lipid bilayer of the nuclear envelope.

label: regulation of meiotic cell cycle
definition: Any process that modulates the rate or extent of progression through the meiotic cell cycle.

label: basal surface of the epidermis
definition: The basal surface of the epidermis in direct contact with the basal lamina.

label: spermatogonium
definition: An euploid male germ cell of an early stage of spermatogenesis. In planaria, the gh4+ stem cell daughter exiting the niche undergoes three rounds of transit amplifying division with incomplete cytokinesis prior to transitioning to terminal differentiation.

label: midline
definition: The median line/ plane of bilateral symmetry along the anteroposterior axis.

label: dorsal-ventral muscle cell
definition: A muscle cell that runs in the transverse plane that connects the dorsal and ventral sides of the animal.

label: regulation of metabolic process
definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of the chemical reactions and pathways within a cell or an organism.

label: nephridiopore
definition: The external opening and terminus of a protonephridium made by a terminal cell.

label: cell cycle
definition: The progression of biochemical and morphological phases and events that occur in a cell during successive cell replication or nuclear replication events. Canonically, the cell cycle comprises the replication and segregation of genetic material followed by the division of the cell, but in endocycles or syncytial cells nuclear replication or nuclear division may not be followed by cell division.

label: cellular component organization
definition: A process that results in the assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a cellular component.

label: afferent neuron
definition: A neuron which conveys sensory information centrally from the periphery.

label: pending final vetting
definition: All definitions, placement in the asserted IS_A hierarchy and required minimal metadata are complete. The class is awaiting a final review by someone other than the term editor.

label: anatomical structure
definition: Material anatomical entity that is a single connected structure with inherent 3D shape generated by coordinated expression of the organism's own genome.

label: anatomical structure
definition: Material anatomical entity that is a single connected structure with inherent 3D shape generated by coordinated expression of the organism's own genome.

label: ciliated epithelium
definition: Epithelium bearing vibratile cilia on the free surface.

label: cell-cell adhesion
definition: The attachment of one cell to another cell via adhesion molecules.

label: sperm duct epithelial cell
definition: Ciliated epithelial cells comprising the sperm ducts.

label: testis nerve plexus
definition: Nerve plexus surrounding the testis.

label: cellular component organization or biogenesis
definition: A process that results in the biosynthesis of constituent macromolecules, assembly, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of a cellular component.

label: electrically signaling cell
definition: A cell that initiates an electrical signal and passes that signal to another cell.

label: metadata complete
definition: Class has all its metadata, but is either not guaranteed to be in its final location in the asserted IS_A hierarchy or refers to another class that is not complete.

label: positive regulation of cell cycle process
definition: Any process that increases the rate, frequency or extent of a cellular process that is involved in the progression of biochemical and morphological phases and events that occur in a cell during successive cell replication or nuclear replication events.

label: pharynx primordium
definition: This primordium develops into pharynx

label: pharynx muscle cell
definition: muscle cell which is part of the pharynx

label: negative regulation of transferase activity
definition: Any process that stops or reduces the rate of transferase activity, the catalysis of the transfer of a group, e.g. a methyl group, glycosyl group, acyl group, phosphorus-containing, or other groups, from a donor compound to an acceptor.

label: generically dependent continuant
definition: A continuant that is dependent on one or other independent continuant bearers. For every instance of A requires some instance of (an independent continuant type) B but which instance of B serves can change from time to time.

label: embryonic cell
definition: A cell of the embryo.

label: nu neoblast
definition: A population of piwi-2+, ston-2+, elav-2+, ptprd-9+ and msi-1+ progenitors that give rise to one or more neuronal (pc-2+, synapsin+) lineages.

label: gland cell
definition: Specialized insunk epithelial cells located in the mesenchyme that participate in mucus secretion. They are characterized by elongated cell bodies with long cytoplasmic projections that terminate between, or penetrate directly throughepithelial cells and form a secretory pore at the surface.

label: zygotene stage spermatocyte
definition: spermatocyte undergoing zygotene

label: positive regulation of signaling receptor activity
definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of signaling receptor activity.

label: orientation
definition: A spatial quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's placement which is defined by the angle between the bearer and an axis, or the angle between the bearer and another object.

label: smooth endoplasmic reticulum
definition: Endoplamic reticulum that does not contain ribosomes, which synthesizes lipids, phospholipids, and steroids.

label: embryonic gut cavity
definition: Cavity encompassed by the embryonic digestive tract, prior to formation of the branched defintive gut.

label: fission fragment
definition: A fragment derived from a spontaneous or induced fission event.

label: pharynx outer nerve plexus
definition: Ring of the pharynx nerve plexus that is proximal to the exterior surface.

label: stalk
definition: A thin, flexible rod that anchors an egg capsule to a solid substrate.

label: meiotic S phase spermatocyte
definition: spermatocyte undergoing meiotic S phase

label: anatomical line
definition: A one dimensional, immaterial anatomical entity.

label: meiotic metaphase II
definition: The cell cycle phase, following prophase II, during which chromosomes become aligned on the equatorial plate of the cell as part of meiosis II.

label: regulation of binding
definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of binding, the selective interaction of a molecule with one or more specific sites on another molecule.

label: positively regulated by
definition: inverse of positively regulates

label: negative regulation of kinase activity
definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of kinase activity, the catalysis of the transfer of a phosphate group, usually from ATP, to a substrate molecule.

label: extraembryonic structure
definition: A multicellular anatomical structure that is associated with an embryo and derived from the zygote from which it develops, but which does not contribute to the embryo proper or to structures that are part of the same organism after embryogenesis.

label: anaphase neoblast
definition: neoblast undergoing mitotic anaphase

label: X2 cell
definition: A sorted cell population containing irradiation-sensitive and irradiation-insensitive cells, characterized by weak Hoescht 33342 and calcein-AM staining. X2 cell populations contain neoblasts as well as a variety of lineage-dedicated post-mitotic progenitor cells.

label: embryonic pharynx epithelial cell
definition: foxA1+ epithelial cell contained in the embryonic pharynx.

label: signaling receptor binding
definition: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with one or more specific sites on a receptor molecule, a macromolecule that undergoes combination with a hormone, neurotransmitter, drug or intracellular messenger to initiate a change in cell function.

label: cell division
definition: The process resulting in division and partitioning of components of a cell to form more cells; may or may not be accompanied by the physical separation of a cell into distinct, individually membrane-bounded daughter cells.

label: secretory duct
definition: A tubular structure that transports secreted or excreted substances.

label: connected anatomical structure
definition: Material anatomical entity that is a single connected structure with inherent 3D shape generated by coordinated expression of the organism's own genome.

label: oral opening
definition: The orifice that connects the mouth to the exterior of the body.

label: egg capsule
definition: A proteinaceous, semi-permeable shell housing yolk cells and one or more embryos.Egg capsules are anchored to a substrate via a stalk.

label: gut
definition: The planarian triclad gut contains a central anterior gut branch connected to two posterior gut branches arranged around the pharynx. Secondary gut branches extend laterally from the primary gut branches, while tertiary gut branches extend from the secondary branches. Food and waste enter and exit the gut through the pharynx.

label: meiotic metaphase I
definition: The cell cycle phase, following prophase I, during which chromosomes become aligned on the equatorial plate of the cell as part of meiosis I.

label: negative regulation of developmental process
definition: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the rate or extent of development, the biological process whose specific outcome is the progression of an organism over time from an initial condition (e.g. a zygote, or a young adult) to a later condition (e.g. a multicellular animal or an aged adult).

label: involved in
definition: c involved_in p if and only if c enables some process p', and p' is part of p

label: medial muscle cell
definition: Subset of dorsal-ventral muscle cells located in the medial body region.

label: G1 phase neoblast
definition: neoblast undergoing mitotic G1 phase

label: participates in
definition: a relation between a continuant and a process, in which the continuant is somehow involved in the process

label: primitive ectoderm cell
definition: Primitive ectoderm cells differentiate from the blastomere population, exit the cell cycle and interact to boud the embryo during Stage 2.

label: chemosensory neuron
definition: Any neuron that capable of some detection of chemical stimulus involved in sensory perception.

label: biotype
definition: Organisms sharing a specified genotype or karyotype.

label: in_lateral_side_of
definition: X in lateral side of Y <=> if X is in left side of Y or X is in right side of Y. X is often, but not always a paired structure

label: in_lateral_side_of
definition: X in_lateral_side_of Y <=> if X is in_left_side_of Y or X is in_right_side_of Y. X is often, but not always a paired structure

label: in lateral side of
definition: X in lateral side of Y <=> if X is in left side of Y or X is in right side of Y. X is often, but not always a paired structure

label: in lateral side of
definition: X in_lateral_side_of Y <=> if X is in_left_side_of Y or X is in_right_side_of Y. X is often, but not always a paired structure

label: linear incision
definition: A breach of the epidermis and optionally down into other structures though an insult with a knife or other instrument, such that the movement includes the z direction and one or more of the x y direction.

label: regulation of receptor binding
definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a protein or other molecule binding to a receptor.

label: negative regulation of multicellular organismal process
definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of an organismal process, the processes pertinent to the function of an organism above the cellular level; includes the integrated processes of tissues and organs.

label: euchromatin
definition: A dispersed and relatively uncompacted form of chromatin.

label: editor note
definition: An administrative note intended for its editor. It may not be included in the publication version of the ontology, so it should contain nothing necessary for end users to understand the ontology.

label: involved in positive regulation of
definition: c involved in regulation of p if c is involved in some p' and p' positively regulates some p

label: gastrodermal cell
definition: cell which is part of the gastrodermis

label: cell body
definition: The portion of a cell bearing surface projections such as axons, dendrites, cilia, or flagella that includes the nucleus, but excludes all cell projections.

label: non-material anatomical boundary
definition: A non-material anatomical entity of two dimensions. Anatomical boundaries are contiguous structures.

label: terminally differentiated cell
definition: A post-mitotic, terminally differentiated cell type found in planarian embryos, juveniles and/or adult animals.

label: temporal interpretation
definition: An assertion that holds between an OWL Object Property and a temporal interpretation that elucidates how OWL Class Axioms that use this property are to be interpreted in a temporal context.

label: transverse commissure
definition: Axon tracts from ganglia that cross the midline, connecting the two ventral nerve cords.

label: non-membrane-bounded organelle
definition: Organized structure of distinctive morphology and function, not bounded by a lipid bilayer membrane. Includes ribosomes, the cytoskeleton and chromosomes.

label: eye cell
definition: cell which is part of the eye

label: multicellular organismal reproductive process
definition: The process, occurring above the cellular level, that is pertinent to the reproductive function of a multicellular organism. This includes the integrated processes at the level of tissues and organs.

label: capable of regulating
definition: Holds between c and p if and only if c is capable of some activity a, and a regulates p.

label: anatomical system
definition: Multicellular, connected anatomical structure that has multiple organs as parts and whose parts work together to achieve some shared function.

label: TrpA+ central nervous system neuron
definition: A subset of TrpA+ neurons, located medially in the cephalic ganglia, whose formation is dependent on function of runt-1 and ap2.

label: antero-lateral region
definition: Anatomical region that overlaps the anterior and lateral regions of a body or body part.

label: pharynx outer longitudinal muscle cell
definition: Pharynx muscle fibers running anteroposterior which lie just underneath the apical, cilaited portion of the outer epithelium.

label: ventral epidermis
definition: Single cell layer of ventral, post-mitotic, heavily ciliated epithelial cells

label: multicellular organism reproduction
definition: The biological process in which new individuals are produced by one or two multicellular organisms. The new individuals inherit some proportion of their genetic material from the parent or parents.

label: prophase germ cell cyst
definition: germ cell cyst undergoing mitotic prophase

label: protein binding
definition: Interacting selectively and non-covalently with any protein or protein complex (a complex of two or more proteins that may include other nonprotein molecules).

label: embryonic gut cell
definition: Dispersed, phagocytic gut cells that appear during Stage 4 and ultimately generate a honeycomb-like lattice surrounding the central gut cavity in Stage 5 embryos. Early embryonic gut cell specific transcripts are expressed from Stage 4-6, and are downregulated during Stage 7.

label: wedge amputation
definition: A piece of tissue removed from the lateral margin at any given point that extendes interiorly to more medial structures.

label: signal transduction
definition: The cellular process in which a signal is conveyed to trigger a change in the activity or state of a cell. Signal transduction begins with reception of a signal (e.g. a ligand binding to a receptor or receptor activation by a stimulus such as light), or for signal transduction in the absence of ligand, signal-withdrawal or the activity of a constitutively active receptor. Signal transduction ends with regulation of a downstream cellular process, e.g. regulation of transcription or regulation of a metabolic process. Signal transduction covers signaling from receptors located on the surface of the cell and signaling via molecules located within the cell. For signaling between cells, signal transduction is restricted to events at and within the receiving cell.

label: blastomere
definition: An undifferentiated, cycling embryonic cell in Stage 1-5 embryos that expresses piwi-1, numerous adult asexual neoblast enriched genes, and early embryo enriched genes. Blastomeres give rise to temporary embryonic tissues during Stage 2, continue dividing asynchronously in the embryonic wall, and ultimately give rise to neoblasts and adult lineage progenitors beginning in Stage 5.

label: positive regulation of cell cycle
definition: Any process that activates or increases the rate or extent of progression through the cell cycle.

label: reproductive organ
definition: An organ involved in reproduction

label: anaphase oogonial cell
definition: oogonial cell undergoing mitotic anaphase

label: medial-external axis
definition: An anatomical axis that extends from the center of the body outwards or externally.

label: meiotic cell cycle phase
definition: One of the distinct periods or stages into which the meiotic cell cycle is divided. Each phase is characterized by the occurrence of specific biochemical and morphological events.

label: cuneate
definition: A shape quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer's being narrowly triangular, wider at the apex and tapering toward the base.

label: meiotic prophase I
definition: The cell cycle phase which is the first stage of meiosis I and during which chromosomes condense and the two daughter centrioles and their asters migrate toward the poles of the cell.

label: dorsal epidermis
definition: Single cell layer of dorsal, post-mitotic, epithelial cells containing the dorsal stripe.

label: synaptic vesicle
definition: A secretory organelle, typically 50 nm in diameter, of presynaptic nerve terminals; accumulates in high concentrations of neurotransmitters and secretes these into the synaptic cleft by fusion with the 'active zone' of the presynaptic plasma membrane.

label: primitive ectoderm surface
definition: The apical surface of the single layered primitive ectoderm that is in contact with the environment.

label: presynaptic terminal
definition: Terminal inflated portion of the axon, containing the specialized apparatus necessary to release neurotransmitters. The axon terminus is considered to be the whole region of thickening and the terminal bouton is a specialized region of it.

label: sperm duct
definition: A network of tubes that transport sperm from the testes to the seminal vesicles. Tubes connect each testis to ducts that run along the ventral nerve cords. The ducts bifurcate immediately posterior to the pharynx, where they connect to the seminal vesicles.

label: photoreceptor neuron
definition: Bipolar photoreceptor neurons with dendritic projections into the optic cup and axons that innervate the underlying brain.

label: pharynx inner epidermal cell
definition: Epithelial cells lining the inside of the pharynx. In Smed, distally located cells are heavily ciliated.

label: extracellular negative regulation of signal transduction
definition: Any negative regulation of signal transduction that takes place in extracellular region.

label: regulation of multi-organism process
definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a multi-organism process, a process in which an organism has an effect on another organism of the same or different species.

label: neural progenitor cell
definition: Neoblasts and their differentiating daughters implicated in maintenance and regeneration of different tissues in the nervous system.

label: derives into
definition: a relation between two distinct material entities, the old entity and the new entity, in which the new entity begins to exist when the old entity ceases to exist, and the new entity inherits the significant portion of the matter of the old entity

label: regulation of signaling receptor activity
definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a signaling receptor activity. Receptor activity is when a molecule combines with an extracellular or intracellular messenger to initiate a change in cell activity.

label: peripheral nervous system neuron
definition: Any neuron that is part of a peripheral nervous system.

label: negative regulation of mitotic cell cycle
definition: Any process that stops, prevents or reduces the rate or extent of progression through the mitotic cell cycle.

label: genital atrium
definition: A chamber where egg capsules are formed. One or more zygotes and yolk cells produced by the vitelline glands collect in the genital atrium; glands surrounding the genital atrium produce the egg capsule shell.

label: intracellular membrane-bounded organelle
definition: Organized structure of distinctive morphology and function, bounded by a single or double lipid bilayer membrane and occurring within the cell. Includes the nucleus, mitochondria, plastids, vacuoles, and vesicles. Excludes the plasma membrane.

label: anterior tip
definition: The anterior-medial region of the head margin.

label: negative regulation of nuclear division
definition: Any process that stops, prevents, or reduces the frequency, rate or extent of nuclear division, the partitioning of the nucleus and its genetic information.

label: positive regulation of catalytic activity
definition: Any process that activates or increases the activity of an enzyme.

label: anchor cell
definition: Specialized epithelial cell located along the dorsoventral margin that surrounds the viscid and releasing gland cells.

label: membrane part
definition: Any constituent part of a membrane, a double layer of lipid molecules that encloses all cells, and, in eukaryotes, many organelles; may be a single or double lipid bilayer; also includes associated proteins.

label: part_of
definition: a core relation that holds between a part and its whole

label: part of
definition: a core relation that holds between a part and its whole

label: part of
definition: a core relation that holds between a part and its whole

label: adenal rhabdite
definition: Rhabdites that are located basally to the epidermis, in the mesenchyme. In Smed these are present in cells likely on their way to becoming part of the mature epidermis.

label: metabolic process
definition: The chemical reactions and pathways, including anabolism and catabolism, by which living organisms transform chemical substances. Metabolic processes typically transform small molecules, but also include macromolecular processes such as DNA repair and replication, and protein synthesis and degradation.

label: apical side
definition: Anatomical side that is located on the apical end of an organism or structure.

label: secretory cell
definition: A cell that specializes in controlled release of one or more substances.

label: pharynx inner epithelium
definition: Heavily ciliated epidermal cells covering the inner surface of the pharynx shaft.

label: submuscular nerve plexus
definition: Plexus of nerves that innervate the body wall musculature.

label: plug fragment
definition: A 3D piece of tissue, usually though the whole depth of the animal encompassing both dorsal and ventral sides, often made with a biopsy punch.

label: causally related to
definition: This relation groups causal relations between material entities and causal relations between processes

label: proximal tubule
definition: Ciliated epithelial cells form tubules, generating coiled, branching units terminating in flame bulbs. Tubules are formed via intercellular junctions between two epithelial cells. Proximal tubules are connected to non-ciliated distal tubules within the parenchyma.

label: S phase oogonial cell
definition: oogonial cell undergoing mitotic S phase

label: adjacent to
definition: x adjacent to y if and only if x and y share a boundary.

label: adjacent to
definition: x adjacent_to y iff: x and y share a boundary

label: adjacent to
definition: x adjacent to y if and only if x and y share a boundary.

label: adjacent to
definition: x adjacent_to y iff: x and y share a boundary

label: adjacent_to
definition: x adjacent to y if and only if x and y share a boundary.

label: adjacent_to
definition: x adjacent_to y iff: x and y share a boundary

label: parasagittal orientation
definition: An orientation quality inhering in a bearer by virtue of the bearer having a position that is in the parasagittal plane, which runs longitudinally, and is never medial.

label: is a defining property chain axiom where second argument is reflexive
definition: If R <- P o Q is a defining property chain axiom, then (1) R -> P o Q holds and (2) Q is either reflexive or locally reflexive. A corollary of this is that P SubPropertyOf R.

label: interphase
definition: The cell cycle phase following cytokinesis which begins with G1 phase, proceeds through S phase and G2 phase and ends when prophase of meiosis or mitosis begins. During interphase the cell readies itself for meiosis or mitosis and the replication of its DNA occurs.

label: physical object quality
definition: A quality which inheres in a continuant.

label: epithelial cell
definition: A cell that is usually found in a two-dimensional sheet with a free surface. The cell has a cytoskeleton that allows for tight cell to cell contact and for cell polarity where the apical part is directed towards the lumen and the basal part to the basal lamina.

label: diplotene
definition: The cell cycle phase which follows pachytene during prophase I of meiosis, during which the homologous chromosomes begin to separate and the synaptonemal complex dissolves.

label: binding
definition: The selective, non-covalent, often stoichiometric, interaction of a molecule with one or more specific sites on another molecule.

label: regulation of mitotic cell cycle
definition: Any process that modulates the rate or extent of progress through the mitotic cell cycle.

label: curator note
definition: An administrative note of use for a curator but of no use for a user

label: sensory cell
definition: A cell that performs a sensory function.

label: postpharyngeal fragment
definition: A fragment derived from two postpharyngeal amputations, removing the anterior region and the tail tip.

label: prophase spermatogonium
definition: spermatogonium undergoing mitotic prophase

label: cell cycle process
definition: The cellular process that ensures successive accurate and complete genome replication and chromosome segregation.

label: chemical wound
definition: An intentional wound produced by non-autonomous chemical means.

label: fertilization
definition: The union of gametes of opposite sexes during the process of sexual reproduction to form a zygote. It involves the fusion of the gametic nuclei (karyogamy) and cytoplasm (plasmogamy).

label: S phase
definition: The cell cycle phase, following G1, during which DNA synthesis takes place.

label: positive regulation of cellular component organization
definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of a process involved in the formation, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of cell structures, including the plasma membrane and any external encapsulating structures such as the cell wall and cell envelope.

label: positive regulation of protein binding
definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of protein binding.

label: circular muscle cell
definition: Body wall muscle fibers arrayed around the dorsoventral axis. Upon regeneration, these are thought to be produced de novo in the blastema.

label: anatomical axis
definition: A straight line through space, intersecting an anatomical entity.

label: adult hermaphrodite
definition: A fully formed, sexually mature organism that reproduces through cross-fertilization.

label: pigment cell
definition: A pigment cell is a cell that contains pigment granules.

label: Stage 8
definition: A stage of Smed embryonic development defined by a unique gene expression signature and morphology, 13 - 15 days post-egg capsule deposition at 20˚C. Organogenesis and organ maturation continues. Hatching.

label: posterior surface
definition: Anatomical surface that is located on the posterior side of the body or body part.

label: parapharyngeal region
definition: Region of the animal lateral to and surrounding the pharynx.

label: tuba
definition: A sperm storage organ located immediately posterior to the ovary, at the anterior end of the oviduct. Oocytes exiting the ovary are fertilized in the tuba as they enter the oviduct.

label: extracellular space
definition: That part of a multicellular organism outside the cells proper, usually taken to be outside the plasma membranes, and occupied by fluid.

label: optic nerve
definition: A neuron projection bundle that connects the retina or its analog in the eye with the brain. This includes the vertebrate optic nerve (not truly a nerve) as well as analogous structures such as the Bolwig nerve in Drosophila.

label: positive regulation of signaling
definition: Any process that activates, maintains or increases the frequency, rate or extent of a signaling process.

label: Stage 3
definition: A stage of Smed embryonic development defined by a unique gene expression signature and morphology, 2 - 4 days post-egg capsule deposition at 20˚C. Dispersed blastomere cleavage in the embryonic wall of nascent spheres. Yolk ingestion into the gut cavity.

label: regulation of organelle organization
definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a process involved in the formation, arrangement of constituent parts, or disassembly of an organelle.

label: superficial to
definition: Near the outer surface of the organism. Thus, skin is superficial to the muscle layer.

label: superficial_to
definition: Near the outer surface of the organism. Thus, skin is superficial to the muscle layer.

label: activity directly regulates activity of
definition: Holds between molecular entities A and B where A can physically interact with B and in doing so regulates a process that B is capable of.  For example, A and B may be gene products and binding of B by A regulates the kinase activity of B.

label: developmentally preceded by
definition: Candidate definition: x developmentally related to y if and only if there exists some developmental process (GO:0032502) p such that x and y both participates in p, and x is the output of p and y is the input of p

label: epidermal rhabdite
definition: Rhabdites located within epidermal cells.

label: intracellular organelle
definition: Organized structure of distinctive morphology and function, occurring within the cell. Includes the nucleus, mitochondria, plastids, vacuoles, vesicles, ribosomes and the cytoskeleton. Excludes the plasma membrane.

label: Hyman vesicle
definition: PROG-2-5 positive granules that range in size from 0.5um to 1um present in epithelia and epithelia progenitor cells. These are distinct from rhabdites.

label: regulation of signaling
definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of a signaling process.

label: mitotic cell cycle
definition: Progression through the phases of the mitotic cell cycle, the most common eukaryotic cell cycle, which canonically comprises four successive phases called G1, S, G2, and M and includes replication of the genome and the subsequent segregation of chromosomes into daughter cells. In some variant cell cycles nuclear replication or nuclear division may not be followed by cell division, or G1 and G2 phases may be absent.

label: organelle fission
definition: The creation of two or more organelles by division of one organelle.

label: mitotic prophase
definition: The cell cycle phase which is the first stage of M phase of mitosis and during which chromosomes condense and the two daughter centrioles and their asters migrate toward the poles of the cell.

label: extracellular region
definition: The space external to the outermost structure of a cell. For cells without external protective or external encapsulating structures this refers to space outside of the plasma membrane. This term covers the host cell environment outside an intracellular parasite.

label: plug shaped
definition: A shape that is in the form of a plug, being tube-like and expanded on one end.

label: interneuron
definition: Most generally any neuron which is not motor or sensory. Interneurons may also refer to neurons whose axons remain within a particular brain region as contrasted with projection neurons which have axons projecting to other brain regions.

label: optic cup progenitor cell
definition: A progenitor cell that gives rise to optic cup cells of the eye.

label: regulation of phosphorylation
definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of addition of phosphate groups into a molecule.

label: 2-D shape
definition: A shape that inheres in a 2 dimensional entity, such as a cross section or projection of a 3 dimensional entity.

label: ventro-lateral region
definition: Anatomical region that overlaps the ventral and lateral regions of a body or body part.

label: cytoplasmic part
definition: Any constituent part of the cytoplasm, all of the contents of a cell excluding the plasma membrane and nucleus, but including other subcellular structures.

label: capable of part of
definition: c stands in this relationship to p if and only if there exists some p' such that c is capable_of p', and p' is part_of p.

label: capable of part of
definition: c stands in this relationship to p if and only if there exists some p' such that c is capable_of p', and p' is part_of p.

label: mechanoreceptor cell
definition: A cell specialized to transduce mechanical stimuli and relay that information centrally in the nervous system.

label: directly regulates
definition: Process(P1) directly regulates process(P2) iff: P1 regulates P2 via direct physical interaction between an agent executing P1 (or some part of P1) and an agent executing P2 (or some part of P2).  For example, if protein A has protein binding activity(P1) that targets protein B and this binding  regulates the kinase activity (P2) of protein B then P1 directly regulates P2.

label: blastema
definition: A regenerating tissue composed of a proliferative mass of undifferentiated progenitor cells from which new differentiated structures arise.

label: has potential to directly develop into
definition: x has potential to directly develop into y iff x directly develops into y or x is capable of directly developing into y

label: meiotic anaphase II spermatocyte
definition: spermatocyte undergoing meiotic anaphase II

label: independent continuant
definition: A continuant that is a bearer of quality and realizable entity entities, in which other entities inhere and which itself cannot inhere in anything.

label: dorso-lateral region
definition: Anatomical region that overlaps the dorsal and lateral regions of a body or body part.

label: posterior pole
definition: Distinct posterior cluster of muscle cells located at the midline which express wnt1.

label: outer longitudinal muscle cell
definition: Body wall muscle fibers arrayed along the anteroposterior axis. Upon regeneration, these muscles are thought to be established from truncated pre-existing fibers.

label: regulates
definition: process(P1) regulates process(P2) iff: P1 results in the initiation or termination of P2 OR affects the frequency of its initiation or termination OR affects the magnitude or rate of output of P2.

label: regulates
definition: process(P1) regulates process(P2) iff: P1 results in the initiation or termination of P2 OR affects the frequency of its initiation or termination OR affects the magnitude or rate of output of P2.

label: thin fragment
definition: A longitudinal fragment lacking a midline and medial structures.

label: meiotic anaphase I stage spermatocyte
definition: spermatocyte undergoing meiotic anaphase I

label: regulation of kinase activity
definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of kinase activity, the catalysis of the transfer of a phosphate group, usually from ATP, to a substrate molecule.

label: dorsal-ventral axis
definition: Axis that runs along the short axis of the animal, perpendicular to the anteroposterior axis, running from the dorsal (back) side of the animal to the ventral (belly) side of the animal. This axis splits anterior and posterior regions of the animal to either side.

label: dorsal-ventral axis
definition: An axis that is approximately perpendicular to the anterior-posterior axis and that extends through the horizontal plane of the body.

label: S phase oogonial stem cell
definition: oogonial stem cell undergoing mitotic S phase

label: chromosome_part
definition: This is a manufactured term, that serves the purpose of allow the parts of a chromosome to have an is_a path to the root.

label: regulation of reproductive process
definition: Any process that modulates the frequency, rate or extent of reproductive process.

label: sperm duct lumen
definition: Anatomical space enclosed by the sperm duct epithelium.

label: eye
definition: An organ that detects light.

label: protonephridial lumen
definition: lumen which is part of the protonephridia

label: nuclear lumen
definition: The volume enclosed by the nuclear inner membrane.

label: prophase spermatogonial stem cell
definition: spermatogonial stem cell undergoing mitotic prophase

label: positive regulation of meiotic cell cycle
definition: Any process that activates or increases the frequency, rate or extent of progression through the meiotic cell cycle.

label: gastrodermis surface
definition: The surface of the gastrodermis in contact with the gut lumen.

label: spermatocyte
definition: A tektin-1+ male germ cell that develops from spermatogonia. The euploid primary spermatocytes undergo meiosis and give rise to the haploid secondary spermatocytes which in turn give rise to spermatids.

label: early female germ cell
definition: A premeiotic female germ cell (i.e., a diploid female germline stem cell or transit amplifying oogonial cell).

label: pigment cup cell
definition: Non-neuronal, pigmented cells arrayed along the proximal side of the optic cup.

label: developmentally succeeded by
definition: Inverse of developmentally preceded by

label: neurite
definition: Cell appendage of the neuron which includes the axon and the dendrite.

label: directly positively regulates
definition: Process(P1) directly postively regulates process(P2) iff: P1 positively regulates P2 via direct physical interaction between an agent executing P1 (or some part of P1) and an agent executing P2 (or some part of P2).  For example, if protein A has protein binding activity(P1) that targets protein B and this binding positively regulates the kinase activity (P2) of protein B then P1 directly positively regulates P2.

label: bipolar neuron
definition: A type of interneuron that has two neurites, usually an axon and a dendrite, extending from opposite poles of an ovoid cell body.

label: cilium
definition: A specialized eukaryotic organelle that consists of a filiform extrusion of the cell surface and of some cytoplasmic parts. Each cilium is largely bounded by an extrusion of the cytoplasmic (plasma) membrane, and contains a regular longitudinal array of microtubules, anchored to a basal body. The longitudinal array of microtubules are almost always in a 9+2 array with 2 microtubles in the central cilia bundle and 9 sets of doublet microtubules around the perimeter. The exception to this arrangement is spermatazoa flagella, which have a 9+1 array in planarians.
